('792', 'b6649fb6-d4cc-477e-ae8d-39145fb46d06', 'poi āwhiowhio', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:18:56.360751+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro swung whistling gourd', 'A hollowed out gourd (hue) with one to three holes, swung around creating a whistling, chattering sound that resembled birds.'),
('820', 'daec749f-9b0f-4020-a7a1-e9a1fd5e535b', 'contrabass flute', '1', '0', '2016-12-13 23:28:08.885819+00', '', ''),
('168', '7d6964ff-b1f5-472b-bdd7-b53de3739ad3', 'tubular bells', '3', '0', '2019-08-19 14:52:26.858506+00', 'Orchestral chimes', 'Larger orchestral version of chimes, closed top hollow metal tubes are set in a stand with a damper operated by pedals, they are tuned at a definite pitch and played with mallets.'),
('805', '676c2b33-388a-48e6-8892-e588ba4dc129', 'three-hole pipe', '1', '0', '2017-05-04 20:35:15.834608+00', 'european 11th century pipe', 'Ancient pipe originating in Europe, with analogies all over the world, it is often combined with tabor drums.'),
('804', 'b6c87b0e-5f2b-49a4-bc0e-457e0e4951b9', 'saduk', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 15:10:39.428787+00', '', 'A cross between a saxophone and a duduk invented and played by Alexander Berne.'),
('790', '5ed5bf1f-ca26-4aeb-b4dd-88a52b1a17e7', 'pahū pounamu', '3', '0', '2017-05-24 20:12:19.374908+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro gong made of jade and bone', 'Gong made of pounamu; greenstone and pilot-whale bone with a striker made of akeake, a hardwood.'),
('125', '4573bc1b-9388-47d6-b184-ed8a4d1fb47e', 'telharmonium', '4', '0', '2023-12-13 20:19:10.20427+00', 'gigantic electronic organ transmitted through telephone wires.', 'Considered the first electromechanical musical instrument, an early electronic organ.'),
('791', '2e345a93-045e-403a-80a9-4c6835c3a49e', 'pūrerehua', '5', '0', '2023-12-13 20:29:18.085384+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro bullroarer', 'Made of wood, bone or stone, it has a long string attached. When spun around it produces a deep, loud whizzing sound that can be heard from far away.'),
('801', '0e7f913b-4451-45dd-bbd6-004c5226b1ef', 'birch lur', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 18:32:45.586321+00', 'wooden natural brass', 'Known from the Viking age, this natural brass trumpet/horn was made of wood or birch bark.'),
('800', 'b0818d20-2065-4e4b-bce2-21ffa5389b07', 'bronze lur', '1', '0', '2018-03-26 15:05:08.345886+00', 'Bronze age natural brass', 'Chiefly Scandinavian, these bronze age natural brass horns were ritualistically buried in pairs.'),
('863', '938c3958-7a02-4b36-866d-8a3f1b1d589e', 'tumutumu', '3', '0', '2019-02-16 09:31:00.826661+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro ancient struck idiophone', 'Made of resonating stone, wood or bone with a striker of stone, bone or hardwood, this ancient instrument was used for rhythm during chanting.'),
('810', 'd0feefd4-147a-4ed9-a07c-c267b436f47f', 'temür khuur', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 18:43:38.363803+00', 'steel Mongolian jews harp', 'Used in folk medicine and shamanistic rituals.'),
('999', '08a63d8e-0e93-4609-8555-c8cdf35fcf38', 'kacapi', '2', '0', '2019-11-06 21:24:44.646147+00', 'Family of Sundanese string zithers', 'There are two kinds, boat shaped mother and child ones, originally made of a single piece of wood and descended from the kacapi pantun as used in epic story. And a flat box-zither made of wood used from the 1950s and in experimental music.'),
('811', '26ed69bd-3828-4c49-8e74-0fb4399a06d3', 'khulsan khuur', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:55:38.166896+00', 'bamboo mongolian jews harp', 'Used for folk songs, particularly by young girls.'),
('796', '8e1cadfb-6f00-49f7-ad1e-b2fc0482b69c', 'gizmo', '5', '0', '2023-12-13 15:31:32.918219+00', 'electric guitar/bass effect device', 'An effects device to be clamped on the bridge, it produces “synthesizer-like” sounds.'),
('818', '3df89368-10e2-4a3a-878a-88ec1a17ccfd', 'härjedalspipa', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:12:22.165633+00', 'fipple flute from Härjedalen, Sweden', 'Six holed fipple flute used traditionally in pastoral settings like its cousin the spilåpipa.'),
('271', '0fe1a768-45ba-49e4-8363-14db8e73ca85', 'cymbal', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:50:34.003945+00', '', 'Various types of cymbal. Also called chũm chọe.'),
('813', 'b975e1d8-8508-436b-a5ac-9c4116fd195d', 'analog synthesizer', '4', '0', '2023-12-13 20:03:48.364143+00', 'uses analogue circuits to produce sound', 'Using analogue circuits and techniques to produce sound electronically, the first types where created in the 1920s with thermionic valves and other electromechanical machineries.'),
('814', 'ed8f3295-0d30-4406-a08b-ec259a4b58bc', 'ondioline', '4', '0', '2023-12-13 20:19:49.076607+00', 'early analogue synth with various sounds and vibrato keyboard', 'One of the first analogue synths, it had a filter bank with 15 sliders for different sounds, and a “vibrato” inducing keyboard based on the ondes Martenot’s.'),
('52', 'f68936f2-194c-4bcd-94a9-81e1dd947b8d', 'guitar family', '7', '0', '2023-12-13 20:28:19.622492+00', 'DO NOT USE', 'Please help move wrongly credited relationships from this, most if not almost all should probably just be guitar with credit (guitars).'),
('931', 'd50ba107-4930-4e0b-8b3f-ffbea4a1ade1', 'ghaychak', '2', '0', '2024-08-09 14:28:30.562897+00', 'Persian double-chambered bowl lute', 'Having 4 metal strings, it is carved from a single piece of wood into a particular shape similar to the Sarinda, it has 3 soundholes, two on each side of the short neck and one under the bridge which is membrane-covered.<br /> Not to be confused with the Uyghur spike fiddle <a href=/instrument/0d766870-3021-47ce-bd51-78d2d2484e1b>ghijak</a>.'),
('864', '925959ba-97d4-4e6f-b9dc-3ba8c4a773c4', 'pahū', '3', '0', '2017-05-25 09:32:19.4893+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro large signalling drum', 'Logs or thick planks up to 9 meters long used as signalling drums, as gongs for both war and peace. Even living hollowed trees have been used as pahū.'),
('867', '3158f700-4e47-4cc5-b641-228b0c5e5a4a', 'pākuru', '3', '0', '2017-05-25 16:28:03.219755+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro tapping sticks', 'Two rods, one is held in the mouth, which works as a resonance chamber while chanting and singing, the other is used for tapping and scraping, creating rhythm.'),
('325', '39d6fb0f-35a4-4c0a-b6c8-ca210c43f4a7', 'gumbri', '2', '0', '2022-03-21 10:56:14.902976+00', '3-stringed plucked bass-lute', 'Lute played by Gnawa people, its camel hide covered wooden soundbox has 3 goat gut strings.'),
('1068', '8f03b5fc-1e29-4fc0-9d51-818090dd50b4', 'antara', '1', '0', '2022-08-09 10:38:57.887591+00', 'Andean single row panpipe', 'Used in traditional Andes music, it consists of a single row of pipes.'),
('1116', '27d05e5b-1801-4596-8646-c091ed545fe8', 'tulum', '1', '0', '2023-03-23 19:47:58.852652+00', 'Droneless Turkish bagpipe', 'Used by shepherds and peoples of the southeast Black Sea region, it is droneless with parallel double chanters each with 5 fingerholes.'),
('896', '0f12e34a-b764-4c50-82d4-72436f3f256a', 'renaissance rackett', '1', '0', '2018-02-03 18:22:09.807102+00', 'Renaissance era compact double reed', 'Originating 1590 or earlier and made of wood or ivory, it had nine parallel cylindrical bores joined up at the top and bottom creating a continuous bore like a curled up snake. Its reed is attached to a center pirouette.'),
('507', 'b4804589-9529-482e-86c9-4a288aae193f', 'archlute', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 17:38:10.983718+00', '', 'The archlute is a European plucked string instrument developed around 1600 as a compromise between the very large theorbo and the Renaissance tenor lute.'),
('615', 'c7a69b51-7105-4d4c-ab4a-ec118e24d1f0', 'tenor violin', '2', '0', '2018-02-04 17:13:01.361024+00', '', 'Tuned an octave below the traditional violin and at about half the size of the cello, it has a range between the cello and the viola. It has a longer neck and thinner ribs than the cello.'),
('94', 'b47bdb4e-59ee-42d3-96ef-a1f0fdd61148', 'viola damore', '2', '0', '2018-02-04 22:10:29.456098+00', 'Baroque fretless similar to both viols and violins.', 'While it is fretless and played like the violins a la braccia, it has a flat back, c-holes and sloping shoulders like a viol. From the baroque period, it has up to 14 strings.'),
('422', 'e21ce008-8744-407b-ad7c-5caa3f69e610', 'kanklės', '2', '0', '2018-03-04 13:30:32.363266+00', 'Traditional Lithuanian plucked psaltery', 'Oldest instrument of Lithuania, it is made of a special tree in a trapezoid shape, it has a metalbar and wooden pegs at each side were 5 to 12 strings are strung.'),
('424', 'd96160fe-57f5-4dc0-a6ae-bc05314f9743', 'kantele', '2', '0', '2018-03-07 10:52:42.952339+00', 'Traditional Finnish plucked psaltery', 'Traditional and mythological psaltery of Finland, it comes in two versions; the oldest, a one piece bridge-less psaltery with 5 to 20 originally horsehair, later metal, strings and a modern Concert box-zither variant with a switch mechanism to alter the up to 40 strings sharps and flats.'),
('903', '88dad742-e0b7-4ad4-811d-e32b6d2b847d', 'caixa', '3', '0', '2018-03-07 20:16:45.945567+00', 'Brazilian Samba snare-drum', 'Traditionally used in samba and maracatu, it originates from the European military battalion. It is made of a 30-35 cm diameter metal barrel strung with a synthetic material, upon which a steel wire or guitar string is strung across.'),
('780', 'fd6f9e0b-c720-44e8-81f5-d88831c28dbf', 'claviola', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 18:42:08.83268+00', 'free reed aerophone with pitching pipes', 'Free reed melodica-like instrument that is worn like an accordion, with differing length pipes which control the pitch.'),
('905', 'f96573d5-a52c-44b6-8af4-8a7f010bb2d8', 'hyoshigi', '3', '0', '2018-03-08 19:18:20.255011+00', 'Japanese concussion idiophone', 'Used in traditional kabuki and bunraku theatre, it consists of two hardwood pieces tied together with ornamental cord.'),
('875', '45d888f0-2fc5-4326-9a30-7713cbc39280', 'octoban', '3', '0', '2018-03-19 19:19:23.669226+00', 'racked 4 or 8 tom-toms', 'Small but long tom-toms set in groups of four or eight, they are a common addition in drumsets. Originally made of fibreglass, today also acrylic, aluminium or wood is used, and homemade ones of f.ex PVC are not uncommon.'),
('276', '67115113-23f7-4080-a454-c4575b101c70', 'sênh tiền', '3', '0', '2018-03-10 10:00:50.696739+00', '', 'The sênh tiền is a Vietnamese instrument which is a combination of clappers, a rasp and a jingle, made from three pieces of wood with old Chinese coins attached.'),
('221', '7254d816-5cb5-4399-bbe9-4b7e14e67462', 'banhu', '2', '0', '2018-03-14 16:31:20.058015+00', 'northern coconut huqin', 'The banhu is a Chinese bowed string instrument in the huqin family. It is also called banghu for its use in bangzi opera.'),
('822', '6bcb239b-e739-4d47-81e7-c2eec8e7b1ea', 'chirimía and drum', '6', '0', '2023-12-13 20:29:06.376325+00', 'pair of double-reed and drum. from South America.', 'Much like the pipe and tabor, the chirimía and drum is a South American cousin.'),
('224', '1bf9e39f-5ffc-4588-990b-d48609613f8f', 'morin khuur', '2', '0', '2018-03-15 10:11:46.968801+00', 'traditional bowed Mongol fiddle', 'Important to the Mongolians, it is trapezoid shaped with two traditionally horsehair, now often nylon, strings fastened by wooden pegs at the end which is carved like a horse head.'),
('223', 'b1a367a1-6dde-4357-b7bb-0395dfb6c2dd', 'kokyu', '2', '0', '2018-03-16 14:39:16.910762+00', 'Traditional Japanese bowed spikefiddle.', 'Although similar to and introduced at the same time as the shamisen, it is unique to japan. With ebony neck and coconut body its three (rarely four) strings are played upright with a horsetail bow.'),
('882', '30aeef52-3ebf-405e-9baa-ef6c6f3ef6d5', 'repeater', '3', '0', '2019-08-18 14:47:50.98321+00', 'Nyabinghi smaller pitch drum', 'Also known as kette or keteh, it is the smallest size/pitch drum. It has a tight goat skin membrane and it is struck with the fingertips. Important in the Jamaican Burru music and Rastafari movement, it is part of the Nyabinghi/Akete drums.'),
('929', '18043a39-9b83-4d83-b9a7-76fc9c6dab3f', 'cimbasso', '1', '0', '2018-06-06 20:13:34.13687+00', '19th century bass trombone', 'Its name variously used to describe the serpentone, the ophicleide and the bombardon, the modern cimbasso was developed by instrument making firm Pelitti under instruction guidance by Verdi; it had a forward facing bell and 3 to 6 valves. The modern instrument has a characteristic bend.'),
('781', 'd7dd3b43-50e9-4418-bf7b-f999a80dfa08', 'taonga pūoro', '6', '0', '2018-03-19 20:21:40.986443+00', 'Māori traditional instrument ensemble', 'Traditional musical instruments of the Māori people of New Zealand. Consists of gourds (hue), shell flutes (pu), wooden flutes (koauau), wind roarers and other natural materials.'),
('213', '90086448-eb94-4ee1-a3a6-1412398088b9', 'huqin', '7', '0', '2018-03-20 21:56:21.555485+00', '', 'Chinese family of bowed spike-fiddles, usually with 2, occasionally 3-4 strings, the bodies made of wood and covered with skin occasionally thin wood or made of coconut.'),
('1023', '51e92fd2-e56e-4576-8547-acb63e8b8446', 'Pierrot ensemble', '6', '0', '2020-12-02 15:39:24.482964+00', 'ensemble flute, clarinet, violin, cello and piano', 'Chamber ensemble of five players (flute, clarinet, violin, cello and piano). Originally required for Schönbergs Pierrot Lunaire, it became a fairly common combination for 20th century classical groups.'),
('527', 'ea37234d-a59b-4823-954f-aa499970ca94', 'yaylı tanbur', '2', '0', '2017-01-05 18:21:28.315124+00', 'Turkish bowed lute', 'The yaylı tanbur is a bowed lute from Turkey derived from the older plucked tanbur.'),
('823', '2db86733-2865-4053-ad8c-da93505275cc', 'arpeggione', '2', '0', '2017-01-06 01:33:23.73701+00', 'bass viol with guitar frets and tuning', 'Invented in 1823, it had a body like a medieval fiddle, but had frets and tuning like the guitar.'),
('865', '90bd690b-f86d-4ea3-b87d-f945b1ab9e38', 'tōkere', '3', '0', '2017-05-25 14:27:09.58556+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro castanets', 'Castanets of wood, bone, bivalve shells or even flax leaf.'),
('1200', 'e8b3e285-3193-4b60-89d5-69d4743d67bb', 'Magyar duda', '1', '0', '2024-02-22 21:45:17.833384+00', 'Traditional Hungarian bagpipe', 'Used by shepherds and in pagan lifestyle, it has a double bore chanter with one to 2 drones, historically made of dogskin but today goat is used.'),
('868', '3a3280ea-b231-4083-8d20-9f043ca58808', 'gemshorn', '1', '0', '2017-07-30 19:35:40.506027+00', 'Medieval chamois or goat horn', 'Medieval or possibly older, it was historically made of goat-horns or, less commonly, clay. With only a few holes and a single octave range it was used pastorally. Modern revival variants are more complicated and are usually made of cattle-horn.'),
('879', 'd90655c0-184d-4dd6-852c-c683a11c3b5f', 'oval spinet', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:45:52.951862+00', 'late 17th century oval harpsichord', 'More accurately a virginals, its strings were arranged in a pattern creating an oval shape, allowing for a stronger, more compact configuration. 2 examples survive today.'),
('827', '7a9311bd-24d1-4d46-b83e-80731c8a4332', 'čelo', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 18:29:35.509903+00', 'čelović or csello, counter Serbo-Croatian plucked string instrument', 'Counterpoint member of the Serbo-Coatian tamburica orchestra, it is guitar like like the bugarija. It can have two double strings and two single strings (čelović) but now four single strings are more common (čelo/čelović). The čelović is a different pitch than the čelo.'),
('821', '174e4a7a-dad6-4b3b-95e2-e3010b53a0ca', 'chirimía', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:06:43.201384+00', 'oboe-like double reed from South America', 'A relative of the shawm, it was introduced to central and south-america by the Spanish in the sixteenth and seventeenth century.'),
('824', '24b88b3f-a63e-49a0-94d4-c0b82257d6bd', 'bisernica', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 18:27:17.272828+00', 'prim, small Serbo-Croatian plucked string instrument', 'Smallest member of the Serbo-Croatian tamburica orchestra, it is usually the lead or prim instrument. It can either have one double string and three single strings (prim/bisernica) or two double strings and two single strings (bisernica).'),
('869', '0d30c5ce-ea08-4a9a-8816-549a7abf996a', 'tenora', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:20:59.990816+00', 'Catalonian double reed descendant of shawm', 'Derived from the tenor shawm, it was independently developed in Catalonia by oboe player Andreu Turon in the 19th century. Made of ginjoler wood with a metal cone, it is used in the traditional cobla and sardana music.'),
('870', 'fa084f70-c9de-403f-bf9d-c411e4d2e5b4', 'tarota', '1', '0', '2017-08-03 15:23:43.593302+00', 'Wooden keyless shawm from Catalonia', 'Traditional Catalan double reed of medieval origin. Used for cobla music in the 19th century, it mostly disappeared: current tarotas are a modern re-invention.'),
('871', 'dffe56f5-cd75-4392-ad31-1c3abf2b8e37', 'tible', '1', '0', '2017-08-03 19:17:21.345778+00', 'Catalan valved shawm used in cobla', 'Catalan double-reed, created in the 19th Century by adding valves to the tarota. Used principally for cobla music.'),
('100', '3bccb7eb-cbca-42cd-b0ac-a5e959df7221', 'membranophone', '3', '0', '2019-03-05 19:53:32.955085+00', '', 'Any kind of instrument with membranes, usually variously sized drums.'),
('876', '826a3a61-75ce-4620-9890-241f118d99e9', 'mijwiz', '1', '0', '2017-09-12 21:37:34.646339+00', 'twin bamboo single reed pipe', 'Played using circular breathing, it is made of twin bamboo reeds with five to six holes. From the middle-east, it is used in traditional music and as a accompaniment to belly dancing and dabke.'),
('1006', '81da5ec5-4a2f-4481-b01d-fb8ab9ea116d', 'saron demung', '3', '0', '2019-12-02 22:07:41.941626+00', 'Penultimate pitch saron-family member used in Sundanese gamelan.', 'Called simply demung, it is the largest and deepest pitched of the regular saron.'),
('883', '7e42e637-c7b4-422c-ad56-f7fafbd961bb', 'rubab', '2', '0', '2020-03-16 17:59:45.303174+00', 'Ancient Afghan plucked lute member of the bowed rebab family', 'Related to bowed instrument rebab, it is played in many countries, from India to Afghanistan. Its made of wood and covered with a membrane and has 3 melody strings, 3 drone strings and 11/12 resonance strings.'),
('877', '81b96fc2-932b-4eb7-a17d-b0c4238988e1', 'vuvuzela', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:22:02.845543+00', 'plastic horn', 'Plastic horn often used at football matches in South Africa.'),
('832', '3e444ea5-b48d-48a2-8e6a-13217d443957', 'banjo-ukulele', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:24:24.190005+00', 'banjo ukulele hybrid', 'Small fretted hybrid instrument with a banjo body and a ukulele neck, popular in the 1920-30.'),
('884', '112f9cb7-7d0e-457c-a184-a24b789ab286', 'birbynė', '1', '0', '2017-11-30 12:15:47.875574+00', '', ''),
('885', 'f9159e56-0908-4b37-b0db-7b6bc4872a94', 'yoochin', '2', '0', '2017-12-04 14:04:52.665184+00', 'Mongolian wire-stringed hammered dulcimer', 'Originally introduced to Mongolia from China, it has 13 double wire-strings and a black lacquered wooden soundboard. Traditionally it was only played by townspeople.'),
('887', 'ac40beac-a9c4-46a6-82c5-615182440439', 'tungso', '1', '0', '2017-12-05 21:20:50.502253+00', 'Korean notched end-blown bamboo flute', 'Made of thick aged bamboo, this notched end-blown flute may have had a buzzing membrane.'),
('889', 'cf226d13-3080-4d39-bfbb-ad509989dc14', 'hydraulophone', '5', '0', '2017-12-06 20:31:59.253305+00', 'woodwater flute made with hydraulics', 'Made of tubing with holes that may have everything from none to two reeds, water instead of air comes out of the holes. Sound is produced by covering the holes with fingers, altering the flow of water through the holes.'),
('704', 'ba99bd20-8e61-4246-9d69-685485254e8d', 'laouto', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:31:30.074254+00', 'Greek long-neck lute', 'Differs from other lutes in that its string tension is greater thus sounding more like the oud. From ancient Greece, it was used as an accompaniment to Cretan lyra.'),
('836', '1fb90aa8-2b49-4685-a1e5-03da74531136', 'mandoguitar', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:32:02.660478+00', 'electric guitar / mandolin hybrid', 'Unison course tuned 12 stringed electric guitar body with mandolin neck, it is tuned an octave higher than a conventional guitar, thus having the tonal range of the mandolin. <br /> Not to be confused with flat-backed mandolin which is also sold as mando-guitar.'),
('174', '72ef1be2-d348-4d95-ad39-ff00a4636bd6', 'alto violin', '2', '0', '2018-02-04 17:30:13.610818+00', 'Alto or vertical violin, for French alto credits, choose viola', 'Tuned the same as the viola but larger in size, it is played upright like the cello.'),
('215', '988026a0-2cb7-42bb-9407-9110874fa401', 'erhu', '2', '0', '2018-03-14 13:06:04.61902+00', 'Middle range huqin', 'The erhu is a bowed Chinese instrument with two strings.'),
('902', 'bcca3b4d-85ca-453e-8b5a-86a330b0ac39', 'quadruple reed', '1', '0', '2018-03-19 22:31:53.160297+00', '', ''),
('477', '16f816ec-9ecf-4236-8006-19a4b27797f1', 'tanbur', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:44:37.248428+00', 'Persian/Turkish ancient long-necked lute', 'The ancient ancestor of many related lute like instruments.'),
('873', 'f1c020ff-ec49-452c-a556-eb65381c3795', 'tubulum', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 20:01:09.548537+00', 'PVC pipe instrument', 'Invented (or at least made popular) by Blue Man Group, it is made of alternating length PVC pipes and hit with sticks or flaps. It is popular with street musicians.'),
('591', '23a2775f-4bf3-4432-beb2-97be32b9ef50', 'mirliton', '1', '0', '2019-03-05 19:50:21.383556+00', '', 'Simultaneously a woodwind and membranophone, sound is produced by singing or speaking into a thin buzzing membrane.'),
('932', '0d766870-3021-47ce-bd51-78d2d2484e1b', 'ghijak', '2', '0', '2019-11-24 05:26:23.157326+00', 'Uyghur spike fiddle', 'Not to be confused with the Persian lute <a href=/instrument/d50ba107-4930-4e0b-8b3f-ffbea4a1ade1>ghaychak</a>.'),
('1019', 'f7f486a1-5811-4a13-be6b-1123058b4d3d', 'spike-fiddle', '2', '0', '2020-03-19 01:26:11.007568+00', '', 'Particular type of fiddle, long neck, often few strings and usually with a rather small soundbox, it has a spike at the end.'),
('1069', '7548dc7a-4f44-451e-84b6-b2c673b7e0a1', 'walaycho', '2', '0', '2022-08-09 10:51:48.01876+00', 'Smallest member of charango family', 'Smaller than the charango, it has 10 strings.'),
('80', 'ffaf7204-92f1-4c03-846a-748218ebf2a5', 'mouth harp', '3', '0', '2020-09-18 19:40:34.23849+00', 'Family of mouth plucked idiophones', 'Plucked by the mouth, it consists of a characteristically shaped frame with a metal or bamboo reed (tine). There are many variants around the world.'),
('828', '0a455deb-11be-4f9c-a0e3-81efe262a329', 'berda', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 18:30:07.936875+00', 'begeš, large bass Serbo-Croatian plucked string instrument', 'Bass member of the Serbo-Croatian tamburica orchestra, it is contrabass like. It has four thick metal strings.'),
('1199', '84c0f0f8-a468-4291-99da-f6821e0ac111', 'matstsyanka', '1', '0', '2024-03-02 19:15:18.672021+00', 'Belorussian duda', 'Used since ancient times, it is a smaller half round shape with the chanter in one end and drones in the other, there are two related types; from northern Belarus and east-south Lithuania one drone one chanter both having bowed horns at the end. <br /> Secondly; the macianka duda without horns has 3 drones in one hole instead of one.'),
('410', '3b0b9c99-ea82-4716-8c11-c86c8dd99218', 'cümbüş', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 18:35:33.732791+00', 'Turkish oud-like', 'Created by Zeynel Abidin Cümbüş, who named himself after it, it’s a banjolin-like modern Turkish instrument.'),
('840', 'cc996d06-87dc-420e-9ed7-a52867ca6e1e', 'vibrandoneon', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 18:44:02.317986+00', 'accordina with piano keys', 'Wood accordina with piano keys invented in Italy.'),
('833', 'bac20474-624a-46ce-a517-871eea3486b1', 'bouzar / gouzouki', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:25:44.571938+00', 'hybrid of bouzouki and guitar', 'Guitar-bouzouki hybrid with guitar body and 4 pairs of strings like the bouzouki, developed separately several different luthiers, among them Stefan Sobell (bouzar) and Davy Stuart (gouzouki).'),
('847', 'b34f161a-56ea-4567-b2e4-509238fe7691', 'trikiti', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:21:59.281859+00', 'Basque button accordion', 'Diatonic button accordion used in traditional Basque ensemble.'),
('838', '7ecc30ac-8335-43f0-a168-e19a7b13c2cc', 'German concertina', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:12:24.978346+00', 'Bisonoric concertina', 'More usually square than hexagonal, with long plate reeds.'),
('930', '205acba3-c6aa-4e47-be4c-2be043cfd511', 'plucked idiophone', '3', '0', '2018-06-18 15:21:34.303765+00', '', 'Plucked idiophones have spikes, nails or flexible tongues (lamellae) that are plucked in various ways to produce sound.'),
('835', '8889a04e-467e-4319-9974-4bd77bb6463c', 'guitorgan', '4', '0', '2017-03-21 05:54:34.595984+00', 'el guitar / el organ hybrid', 'Invented in 1966 by vox, and in 1969 by Bob Murrell, it is an electric guitar with electronic organ wiring and knobs added.'),
('114', 'a5479f69-0c46-4bd3-8170-add906b9e688', 'monkey stick', '3', '0', '2023-05-29 00:07:21.030416+00', 'Traditional English percussion stick', 'Homemade combination of a wooden pole with beer bottle tops and other jingles and a hefty boot at the bottom to create thumping bass, it is often decorated with hats, hair or stuffed animals.'),
('845', 'd548d806-cd6b-464e-8b87-cfb5adaedbfb', 'flabiol', '1', '0', '2018-03-28 14:33:29.695439+00', 'Small Catalan fipple flute', 'Small Catalan flageolet used in the cobla ensemble, unlike other tabor-pipes it is also played with both hands.'),
('831', 'bc026c3e-066b-492a-8cd1-b140f75461cf', 'banjolin', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:24:11.587288+00', 'banjo and mandolin/violin hybrid', 'Reinvented several times in different lands, it combines banjo body and neck of mandolin, it is tuned like it and the violin.'),
('841', '9df8eaec-98e9-477b-b356-43f6b96642b3', 'dulcitone', '3', '0', '2021-04-13 14:46:04.387209+00', 'Acoustic keyboard tuning fork idiophone', 'Like a piano, but here keyed hammers hit tuning forks.'),
('776', '463262da-3f12-4175-a78b-f0183946ac12', 'donso ngɔni', '2', '0', '2021-02-02 11:51:32.124995+00', 'West African calabash lute-harp', 'Six-stringed lute-harp from Wassoulou, West Africa. Traditionally played by hunters, its resonator box is made of calabash covered by animal skin.'),
('1014', '9869ff82-9ba5-41a7-b2b2-e19f4e4a1083', 'seni rebab', '2', '0', '2021-08-15 20:21:12.275339+00', 'Medieval Indian evolution of the Afghan (kabuli) rabab', 'Larger, with a longer neck than the kabuli rabab, it has a hide covered soundbox and wooden fingerboard with mostly gut strings, it was developed during medieval times by Tansen, who improved it and gave it metal sympathetic strings.'),
('846', '8251d55c-fa4b-4a2f-90e6-e8259501bc06', 'Tonette', '1', '0', '2017-04-05 21:11:36.441647+00', 'plastic fipple flute', 'introduced in 1938, it was a popular American educational instrument.'),
('852', 'f28b4f77-fc67-4433-a49f-1cdd7708df5a', 'Blaster Beam', '2', '0', '2017-04-18 13:13:43.616752+00', 'long metal bar with strings', 'Very long metal bar fitted with strings and electric pickups, it makes a deep ominous booming sound and is often used in score.'),
('729', 'e5951e63-3d8b-4945-8026-cadb726d4ac8', 'ngɔni', '2', '0', '2021-02-08 22:12:24.349+00', 'West African gourd-lute', 'A lute from West Africa, made of wood or gourd.'),
('693', '67cf878f-d93d-42e8-bf31-e6e51f154bf6', 'violoncello piccolo', '2', '0', '2022-07-09 16:01:38.965594+00', 'for violoncello use cello', 'Baroque string instrument sized between the viola and cello, it typically has five strings.'),
('849', '7a0733b6-5140-49c5-851d-b9f0de21e63d', 'kagurabue', '1', '0', '2022-07-18 18:28:31.48371+00', 'Japanese transverse bamboo flute', 'Used in gagaku, this traditional bamboo flute has six holes.'),
('391', 'b9362496-01a3-4298-b369-84313cec5ee1', 'tambura', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 18:40:08.717899+00', 'Macedonian/Bulgarian long-necked lute', 'Do not confuse with: <ul> <li>Serbo-Croat “tamburica” ensemble.</li> <li>Persian/Turkish ancient things that evolved from “tanbur”.</li> <li>Unrelated Indian drone “tanpura”.</li> <li>Related Indian “pandour”.</li> </ul>'),
('844', 'bfa5b262-34cf-418b-a9c5-b629a24a96ee', 'English flageolet', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:09:29.660012+00', '1800s improved flageolet', 'Meant as an improvement on the flageolet design, the English flageolet had six finger holes in the front and one thumb hole in the back.'),
('850', 'e0b0f1c6-25e9-49b9-8164-131a251e8dce', 'djoza', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:30:42.077283+00', 'ancient Iraqi bowed string instrument', 'Its origins can be sourced almost 5000 years ago, this Iraqi string instrument is the forefather of several instruments around the world. Its name means coconut or acorn, while originally made of walnut, it is today of coconut and fish-skin or heart-membrane.'),
('834', '6dadb008-cb59-40cb-8b3a-a07942ffb818', 'viololyra', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:37:07.153862+00', 'Cretan lyra / violin hybrid', 'Inspired by the violin in 1920, Hellenic luthiers combined parts of the old Cretan lyra with the violin.'),
('842', '999dbad8-5d0a-423c-bef2-6e50e7bcb7c7', 'orphica', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:46:09.624344+00', 'late 18th century portable piano with shoulder strap', 'Portable piano with shoulder strap invented in 1795, it is a descendant of the Baroque Bauchladenspinett and a sort of early precursor of the keytar.'),
('851', 'b34c3736-17fb-4462-a311-3d20539773d8', 'duggi', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:50:35.400769+00', 'indian clay kettle drum', 'Made of clay with two layers of goat skin, it is used as a rhythmic accompaniment to shehnai players and is one of the instruments of the Baul community.'),
('1007', '5b159ed5-2c58-4200-accb-c2ac5c9ace7f', 'saron barung', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 20:02:36.172954+00', 'Middle pitch saron-family member used in Sundanese gamelan.', 'Often called simply saron, it plays the basic, balungan melody.'),
('848', 'c498b4b0-7cbf-4b48-b7f6-18b32df02df1', 'elektronium', '4', '0', '2023-12-13 20:06:11.583518+00', 'electronic keyboard accordion', 'In the form of a piano accordion, the keys control the output, pitch and sound, bellows control only volume. Sold by Hohner since 1952, it has gone through many modernisations through the years.'),
('1008', '2656be9c-b531-4cbb-a5b5-30454054343c', 'saron panerus', '3', '0', '2019-12-02 22:18:15.307368+00', 'Highest pitch saron-family member used in Sundanese gamelan.', 'Called simply panerus, it has seven bronze keys resting on a decorated rancak box. Keys are hit by tabuh mallet with head of buffalo horn.'),
('7', '3590521b-8c97-4f4b-b1bb-5f68d3663d8a', 'cor anglais', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:07:54.019575+00', 'Curved bulb belled transposing oboe', 'While also known as English horn, it is neither a horn nor English, but a transposing member of the oboe family, pitched at F.'),
('854', 'a11e9091-1182-4d79-90a1-dcaa282e4a98', 'jeli ngɔni', '2', '0', '2017-05-03 22:06:20.693096+00', 'West African four-stringed grigot lute', 'Four-stringed banjo-like lute from West Africa, traditionally played by griots. Made of hollowed out wood with an animal hide as membrane.'),
('1201', '95144855-a019-4076-bd2e-95ab461a69d3', 'dudy wielkopolskie', '1', '0', '2024-03-04 17:11:27.348571+00', 'Great Polish bagpipe', 'Originally played together with the special fiddle mazanki, today with prepared violin or solo, it has a single chanter with seven finger holes and a drone pipe folded back on itself twice both ending in curved bells.'),
('894', '19143e79-1a3e-4696-b030-36d379ef59a7', 'harpejji', '2', '0', '2017-12-16 04:18:35.412468+00', 'Electric guitar-piano tapping instrument', 'Effectively a small electric guitar-piano hybrid, it is played by tapping the multiple isometric arranged strings that are stretched over a long flat board.'),
('858', 'fdcacb6d-7f3d-446d-aa65-fff4c9afb7f6', 'hue puruhau', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:14:10.73295+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro large bass gourd', 'Large gourd (hue) with no finger-holes, it is blown like a jug and has a booming bass sound.'),
('859', '0c5e5de9-605c-4487-b454-ef70ef8c1996', 'rōria', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 20:02:40.479757+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro mouth harp', 'Thin quiet mouth harp like instrument made of wood or bone.'),
('862', '908b5372-2a64-4248-8c27-3e9c76951aa1', 'porotiti', '1', '0', '2017-05-24 08:32:35.201029+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro humming discs', 'Whirring, spinning disks of many shapes, sizes and materials. When blown on, they also create a well of different humming sounds.'),
('861', 'f7e7dd09-eef7-4c66-a226-c8eb6ba378e1', 'pūpakapaka', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:21:16.11123+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro long necked conch trumpet', 'A pūtātara with a long wooden mouth piece, it has a deeper timbre than the pūtātara.'),
('857', 'fdc68c28-cc0c-4ae6-bd9e-dd0b68e3cf1a', 'hue puruwai', '3', '0', '2017-05-24 08:32:44.614241+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro shaking gourd', 'Gourd (hue) shakers with seeds intact'),
('856', 'a4f10af3-d440-4ee7-9093-c60a121df41a', 'kōauau ponga ihu', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:15:42.46338+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro tiny gourd nose flute', 'Nose flute made of gourd with two holes. While it is tiny, it has a huge sound.'),
('895', '8659d5b5-6e07-4497-a903-5dd41619492b', 'mandora / gallichon', '2', '0', '2017-12-16 18:43:53.327542+00', '18th century bass lute', 'Invented by European luthiers in the first half of the 18th century, it had 6 to 7 single or double courses of gut strings and a long neck with either sharp or shallow angled pegbox.'),
('866', '9fb5bbba-2ee3-4791-98f5-e256429e353b', 'poi', '3', '0', '2017-05-25 15:04:58.15019+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro flax leaf balls used in dancing', 'Flax leaf balls filled with seeds, swung around to create rhythmic and visual patterns. An important element in the dance also known as poi.'),
('872', 'db6a575f-b581-4176-a1d8-2c0d948b23f5', 'kannel', '2', '0', '2017-08-24 09:26:35.739324+00', 'Traditional Estonian plucked psaltery', 'National symbol of Estonia, related to Finnish kantele. While traditionally a small instrument with 5 to 7 strings, some newer versions are much bigger, with up to 50 strings.'),
('874', '3a6a4d43-ac19-4604-b099-82cc4394fca9', 'boobam', '3', '0', '2017-09-09 15:16:46.363981+00', 'arrangement of bamboo tube-drums', 'Pipes of bamboo with goat or calfskin membranes, the pitches depend largely on tube-lenght, it is the ancestor to the octoban. Modern variants are usually made of wood, plastic or metal with plastic membranes.'),
('853', 'ab2edb77-e1ff-406b-bdf4-7c4d659a554e', 'game console sound chip', '4', '0', '2023-12-13 20:11:49.926389+00', 'sound chip from gaming consoles', 'Sound chip from various video game consoles, computers and similar, used for music, chiefly in bitunes and chiptunes.'),
('886', 'b673ed30-fe14-47b4-9a1b-8b5f77862e7a', 'lap harp', '2', '0', '2017-12-04 16:35:04.12778+00', 'simplified zither', 'Used to teach children how to play, it is a simplified zither shaped like a trapezoid.'),
('514', '996e6514-37a4-4b22-af71-e968f30913fd', 'fife', '1', '0', '2018-01-01 15:22:12.142815+00', '', 'Small, high-pitched, transverse flute, similar to the piccolo, but with a narrower bore.'),
('839', '26b4608d-acc3-46f3-b509-d83bd798e122', 'Anglo concertina', '1', '0', '2021-02-02 11:36:28.128032+00', 'Historical hybrid between English and German style concertinas', 'Bisonoric and button layout like the German, reeds and hexagonal ends like the english, this concertina was created to rival the popular German variant imported into England.'),
('897', 'dd93de8f-c32a-4bcf-8e90-4463c79676ea', 'baroque rackett', '1', '0', '2018-02-03 18:27:16.46387+00', 'Conical bored compact double reed', 'Improved by Johann Christoph Denner sometime around 1730, its coiled snake bore now is conical, in addition it is played through a removable metal curled mouth piece.'),
('860', '1b425878-18c7-4bcd-9129-bed989295e5f', 'te kū', '2', '0', '2018-06-14 20:22:21.311519+00', 'Māori taonga pūoro single string bow', 'also just kū, a mouthbow with a single string, struck with a light implement of bone or wood.'),
('898', '07bffa5f-17a9-4945-bff4-d716af5b6d4e', 'violin octet', '6', '0', '2018-03-19 20:20:39.530133+00', 'New modern streamlined family of violins', 'New Violin Family of eight proportionally-sized violins developed mainly by Carleen Hutchins, each based directly on the standard violin and its acoustic properties, thus their sound is at a more homogeneous pitch near the two middle open strings.'),
('48', '7bd32b95-416f-4244-a98b-1311ec69c7db', 'double bass', '2', '0', '2021-11-04 15:29:47.204538+00', 'Contrabass of modern violin family', 'Known also as contrabass or upright bass, it is the largest and lowest-pitched member of the modern violin family and a principal member of the symphony orchestra.'),
('900', 'e1abddc8-4942-4674-a567-6aeb2f2329ea', 'bass violin', '2', '0', '2018-02-04 23:01:29.164812+00', 'Sixteenth century precursor of the (violon)cello', 'Sixteenth century predecessor of the violoncello, it was fretless with f-holes and had at first three, then later four, strings tuned in fifths.'),
('901', '3e394f5c-374e-447d-8154-c6a1a72d272e', 'Gravikord', '2', '0', '2018-02-08 22:56:47.326713+00', 'Modern 24-stringed stainless steel kora', 'Based on the polyrhythm of the Afrikan kora, kalimba and Japanese koto, it is electro-acoustic with a stainless steel frame with 24 nylon strings and an integral piezoelectric sensor.'),
('878', '2f625ae3-a07c-4ca5-84cf-93dc1a763b07', 'Irish flute', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:14:15.325297+00', '19th century transverse flute', 'Wooden flute of the simple-system type, popular in Irish folk music.'),
('795', '9465df95-c901-4402-a169-7005756fdcaf', 'Guitaret', '4', '0', '2023-12-13 20:12:50.162465+00', 'electric lamellophone', 'Small white electric thumb piano with metal tines and an electromagnetic pickup.'),
('907', '17ed4105-1345-4235-82b2-6fd81f69ee1d', 'zhuihu', '2', '0', '2018-03-21 18:30:53.304994+00', 'Wooden huqin', 'Originating from Henan province, this fretless huqin has the accustomary two strings, but is made of wood.'),
('888', '7b95d4e0-7a5f-4d09-b2fb-700b90322450', 'olifant', '1', '0', '2018-03-26 15:05:47.114348+00', 'Ivory natural brass hunting horn', 'Hunting horn carved out of ivory, it was widely used in Medieval wars to alarm or increase soldiers morale.'),
('855', '79230fb5-5836-4344-88ca-ddbf7cfd7a36', 'txistu', '1', '0', '2018-03-28 14:35:57.254559+00', 'Basque fipple flute', 'Fipple flute that became a symbol for the Basque folk revival.'),
('632', '56c8b6ff-b442-4adf-bd51-b2e26f28338b', 'lamellaphone', '3', '0', '2019-02-04 13:48:52.689685+00', '', 'Lamellophones are a family of musical instruments which have one or more long thin plates - lamella or tongues - which are fixed at one end and free at the other end. The free end is plucked, causing the plate to vibrate.'),
('560', '4809de55-92ba-4bac-b1b0-a609d2d41d18', 'wind synthesizer', '4', '0', '2023-12-13 20:22:31.41381+00', 'synthesizer played like a wind instrument', 'Wind synthesizer or wind controller, it is connected to a MIDI controller and is played like a wind instrument.'),
('807', 'e31dd801-6cc3-49c1-b2f9-fc7700ce5ac1', 'pipe and tabor', '6', '0', '2018-03-19 20:27:43.356046+00', 'pair of flute and drum, each played by one hand', 'Originally an early European combination of a drum (tambourine) and pipe (fipple flute) were pipe was played by one hand and drum beaten by the other. It was chiefly used for dancing music. It has analogies all over the world.'),
('101', '12092505-6ee1-46af-a15a-b5b468b6b155', 'drums (drum set)', '3', '0', '2018-06-21 20:00:24.754804+00', 'Set of drums in modern music', 'Set of drums developed from the 1930s onward, it is used in Jazz, Swing, Rock and Pop music. It consists of snare drum, tom-toms, hi-hats, cymbals and bass drum.'),
('944', 'e5408785-e228-4919-9e79-6f997bcdfea5', 'tube zither', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 17:43:17.330012+00', '', 'A zither with a hollow or vaulted body, it can have several resonators.'),
('1021', '66345913-2e2c-4527-a27d-403f619c3b3d', 'portative', '1', '0', '2020-10-20 11:20:43.916605+00', 'Very small bellows operated pipe organ', 'Constructed in medieval Europe to be as portable as possible, small upright wooden frame with keyboard contains a row of flute-pipes fed air from hand operated bellows.'),
('165', '340b8043-e3c4-443e-afb8-7fce24fe0ce4', 'glockenspiel', '3', '0', '2019-08-19 14:54:07.472016+00', '', 'Common and popular metallophone, usually an arrangement of metal keys or slabs on a wooden resonator box. <br /> For the instrument often used in bell towers, see <a href=/instrument/0d14d4e0-9ac9-4a96-a595-4145d7794082>carillon</a>.<br /> For the instrument called orchestra bell/chime in some languages, see <a href=/instrument/7d6964ff-b1f5-472b-bdd7-b53de3739ad3>tubular bells</a>.'),
('816', 'efca0287-2791-4209-b29b-1019891cb8d2', 'sursingar', '2', '0', '2021-08-15 20:30:42.05781+00', '19th century large North-Indian dhrupad bass-sarod', 'Improved further by Jaffar Khan, it had a wooden soundboard, the fingerboard covered with iron and all strings are steel or bronze.<br /> Less common today, it was used for Dhrupad style music.'),
('935', '6afeed40-2392-43c4-87a0-44d0f58fea6d', 'octobass', '2', '0', '2018-08-11 21:33:23.215074+00', 'Extralarge 3-string Bass', 'Constructed as the uttermost largest member of the violin family, it is up towards 4 meters and has three strings operated by levers and pedals.'),
('936', 'e11d6ef4-857d-462e-b91c-ef9f9f4a2760', 'njarka', '2', '0', '2018-08-15 19:17:42.302289+00', 'Malian single string gourd-fiddle', 'Made of goatskin covered dried gourd, it has a single gut string bowed with a horsehair bow.'),
('942', 'c03b445f-2790-4518-95b8-6b7fd600c6b9', 'saxophone quartet', '6', '0', '2023-12-13 20:29:00.435703+00', '', 'Ensemble of four saxophones, generally SATBar.'),
('938', '9483eb06-fd5a-4792-844f-72bc4cb1c0a1', 'flamenco guitar', '2', '0', '2018-08-20 22:40:15.554881+00', 'Guitar used in flamenco', 'Deriving from the classical guitar, it has many modifications and playing techniques to create a more percussive sound. Originally having wooden tuning pegs like lutes and violins, it has a thinner, lighter build with golpeadores or tapping-plates and less sustain than the classical guitar.'),
('939', 'f05efa5a-f0ac-4839-b2a8-637605026545', 'chitarra battente', '2', '0', '2018-08-26 13:23:27.497207+00', 'Italian strumming 17th century guitar', 'Developed chiefly as a folk instrument for accompanying singing and dancing, its front has a intricately carved soundhole and slants towards the bottom where the 5 double (sometimes triple courses) of thin steel strings are fastened with pins. The back can be rounded or flat.'),
('941', 'efe98275-ad37-44cc-9471-bc0081924a39', 'octavina', '2', '0', '2018-08-26 20:19:46.846507+00', 'Filipino rondalla guitar', 'Originating with the Spanish influence on Filipino culture, it has 14 strings and a short neck with 16 to 20 frets. It is played with its close relative, the laúd.'),
('516', '21468ce3-bad3-4f48-a2ff-01e6b0bc9ca2', '17-string bass koto', '2', '0', '2018-09-01 22:50:19.647909+00', '', 'A koto with 17 rather than 13 strings, sometimes described as a bass koto.'),
('303', '93edb5e2-d047-486f-90f3-809708f7ba2d', 'kèn bầu', '1', '0', '2020-10-20 13:55:34.306924+00', 'Vietnamese double reed', 'Used in the traditional music of Vietnam, it is made of wood with a gourdshaped bell.'),
('904', '586352fa-7129-4324-ad92-367364fa6bc8', 'clapper', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:48:39.843609+00', 'Egyptian ancient clappers', 'Made of wood, bone or metal, this ancient instrument is the forerunner to many other struck idiophones.'),
('145', '23171239-1d9d-4482-b057-1ba884bcfda6', 'musical saw', '5', '0', '2020-11-13 17:24:30.19568+00', 'Bowed metal plaque idiophone', 'Regular or specialised saw used for music, held and bent, it is bowed to produce characteristical glissando.'),
('743', 'bc090764-54f3-4bc4-a4eb-d9ba2bc1afd5', 'bicycle bell', '3', '0', '2018-10-01 16:04:32.755429+00', '', 'Bell as found on bicycles, sound is made by internal spring loaded hammer, not unlike alarm-clock.'),
('768', '1c3a672f-fbde-418c-aa06-cd3fe0d7536e', 'ütőgardon', '2', '0', '2022-03-21 10:57:33.247208+00', 'Hungarian percussion-viol', 'Played in folk music of Hungary and Transylvanian regions, its 3-4 strings are plucked or struck with a stick, and its soundbox is made of thick maple, poplar or willow wood.'),
('442', '25cb4a8d-9928-4102-8933-1cc3b0998efe', 'Marxophone', '2', '0', '2019-01-15 17:32:38.163409+00', '', 'A type of fretless zither.'),
('1000', '3740ddf9-0067-44d6-8634-9787084ae0f8', 'kacapi siter', '2', '0', '2019-11-06 21:55:35.760795+00', 'Box zither used in Sundanese gamelan', 'Inspired by western zithers, it has 20 strings and is flatter than the other kacapis.'),
('286', '9ace3b20-ff09-4a53-b737-79f9dc1ca90b', 'santoor', '2', '0', '2019-01-07 15:37:03.020759+00', 'Traditional Indian dulcimer', 'Ancient hammered dulcimer with trapezoid walnut or maple soundbox, 25 bridges each with 4 strings that are hit by special mallets called mezrab. Used in traditional, folk and mystic Sufi music.'),
('316', '29872747-b9cf-43f5-a258-0997728ed058', 'sáo meò', '1', '0', '2019-01-15 20:00:22.217683+00', '', 'saó ôi (flute of the Muong)'),
('1202', 'f6505e4e-fa59-4194-8d79-fad78d1c33a5', 'dudy podhalanskie', '1', '0', '2024-03-04 17:42:13.007485+00', 'Podhale bagpipe', 'Known since the 16th century, it has 3 drones; one in a separate drone pipe and two in the chanter (which as three channels), it has no bells and is mouthblown.'),
('1070', '7c166511-91b1-4a18-80f8-74122946e6f0', 'ronroco', '2', '0', '2022-08-09 11:08:33.339237+00', 'South American square charango', 'An octave lower than the charango, it is the largest member of the family.'),
('946', '1ed558ad-1628-4e5f-8d14-e18e54375cd5', 'surbahar', '2', '0', '2019-01-23 23:36:48.709685+00', 'Bass sitar', 'Effectively a bass sitar, it has 4 main, 3-4 chikari(drone) and 10-11 resonance strings strung over a wide wooden neck. Made of flat-cut gourd with a possible secondary resonator (tumba) it was invented in 1825 by sitar-player Ghulam Mohammed who wanted a deeper sound.'),
('666', '0f2a75c7-f10b-49cc-8acf-70fc0b5e2c9e', 'khlui', '1', '0', '2019-03-16 10:02:36.849772+00', 'Vertical bamboo duct flute', 'Ancient reedless fipple flute made of bamboo.'),
('953', 'dbd1ec09-34fd-412e-b73b-124e46cf7cdf', 'scraped idiophone', '3', '0', '2019-02-04 16:20:50.35725+00', '', ''),
('775', 'e346ac37-b617-4c12-b54d-d25474b6c7b7', 'tubon', '4', '0', '2023-12-13 18:41:21.741234+00', 'analogue electronic monophonic organ', 'Electronic bass organ, proto-keytar.'),
('44', '8ab40df2-106b-4b9b-a50c-0798ee95da8f', 'melodica', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:16:11.838406+00', 'Free-reed keyboard mouth-organ', 'Popular as a musical education tool, it is usually made of plastic with a keyboard, its free-reed mouthpiece can also have an optional air tube. It has many brand names.'),
('246', 'd7977da9-ed10-441a-b4e3-a64277db2cb6', 'electric sitar', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:30:45.429797+00', 'electric guitar variant of sitar', 'An electric derivation of the sitar, it often features sympathetic strings and a more guitar shaped body.'),
('937', 'cba4f354-f7ff-45fd-a91b-0e8e5e1dba05', 'güira', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:50:42.832709+00', 'Dominican metal scraper', 'Made of metal with many small notches scraped with a brush or hair pick, it is used in merengue típico.'),
('912', 'e954558e-8ec5-4d1e-b89f-23dd907cc483', 'claviorganum', NULL, '0', '2018-03-26 11:11:40.605446+00', 'Fifteenth century organ harpsichord hybrid', 'Popular in the fifteenth century, it was a combination of a pipe organ and harpsichord, often with two keyboards, one for the strings and one for the pipes mounted underneath.'),
('521', 'a6e9129c-63d3-4e38-bcc3-8f4662a8f247', 'baroque trumpet', '1', '0', '2018-03-26 14:25:18.554743+00', '20th century reinvented natural trumpet', 'Based on the natural trumpet used in the 1500s to 1700s, this mid 20th century reinvention lacks valves but may have vents.'),
('1203', '112b11a3-9b39-4ebc-86bd-4c9289e1ec81', 'dudy', '1', '0', '2024-03-22 14:04:42.2517+00', 'Czechian / Bohemian bagpipe', 'Also known as bock, referencing the goatskin bag, it has been in use since atleast 1340s. It has a single drone and chanter with single reeds, modern variants are bellows blown.'),
('772', '3e439f48-e677-4aea-b064-b1436476d7b3', 'txalaparta', '3', '0', '2018-03-28 14:57:47.789406+00', 'Traditional Basque idiophone', 'Traditionally consisting of two long wooden planks with corn-husks attached for vibration and hit with long, thick sticks called Makilak, today the planks are shorter and can be made of many other materials like stone, wood or metal and are hit with shorter, lighter sticks.'),
('916', '7cbd040f-6217-48d0-ac43-3e8ecb4b4b0b', 'bass viol', '2', '0', '2018-04-04 18:16:42.605143+00', 'Bass member of the viol family', 'Most common viol member today, it was the bass-range viol in the original consort.'),
('605', '7b14c118-e243-459c-a18a-0c478a3ea6f4', 'baryton', '2', '0', '2018-04-05 00:59:10.569295+00', 'Bowed with pluckable strings', 'Hybrid between the viol and the bandora, it has an extra set of plucked strings in addition to the bowed ones. Used regularly in Europe until the end of the 18th century.'),
('918', 'fc02e955-db77-4854-908e-efb04b1ab6a3', 'regal', '1', '0', '2018-04-05 15:52:40.075741+00', 'Portable bellowed reed organ', 'Popular in the renaissance, it was small and portable with two bellows and brass reeds.'),
('742', '504f30a8-92b3-444a-82e0-fbeb316b5ded', 'flumpet', '1', '0', '2018-04-10 10:08:13.539666+00', 'Hybrid between trumpet and flugelhorn', 'As long as a trumpet, it shares the piston valve design of both instruments with a mellow sound between the two.'),
('350', '4ddf3737-9ef2-49c4-9de2-697a19884463', 'pipa', '2', '0', '2018-04-16 17:57:04.591542+00', 'Pearshaped chinese lute', 'Chinese pear-shaped plucked lute with four strings and 12 to 26 frets.'),
('395', '1a9bc5e0-b9f4-46df-8b64-4000b2253211', 'theorbo', '2', '0', '2018-04-16 18:12:34.618128+00', 'Extended necked many-stringed lute', 'Developed as an extended range bass-lute in Italy during the late sixteenth century, it has an extended neck with a second pegbox.'),
('765', '44accbb9-f7b4-42ad-9d4b-fce69407ae11', 'glass harp', '3', '0', '2018-04-24 10:27:07.868514+00', 'Musical Glasses', 'Known in Persia as far back as the 14th century, it consists of glass containers, tuned by either being filled with water or later being of different sizes. Played by rubbing dampened fingers on the rims.'),
('940', 'd32661fd-b2d3-4c6d-9daa-96dbeee1e19a', 'octavilla', '2', '0', '2018-08-26 14:30:56.739782+00', 'Spanish melody & strumming guitar', 'Used in Spanish classic and popular music during the late 19th and early 20th century, it together with bandurria and laúd carried the melody in rondas and rondallas. It had six pairs of strings, tuned a fourth lower than bandurria, It fell out of use when contralto bandurria became common.'),
('913', 'c55f5f41-a4e1-4b9a-971a-6f79324cb2a0', 'natural trumpet', '1', '0', '2019-05-28 19:33:04.129725+00', 'Brass valveless ancestor of the modern trumpet', 'Ancestor of the modern trumpet, it is valveless with a mouthpiece and at-least one coil, it has an origin in military use.'),
('43', '63e37f1a-30b6-4746-8a49-dfb55be3cdd1', 'harmonica', '1', '0', '2018-08-31 12:03:20.93469+00', 'mouth organ', 'Used especially in blues, American folk and country, it consists of a rectangle shape with soundholes along the wide side, where air is blown and drawn across free reeds which are mounted on a plate inside.'),
('257', '27cb4a0f-bdfa-4b1d-8b78-3768063154e3', 'đàn tam thập lục', '2', '0', '2019-01-07 15:44:03.160724+00', 'Vietnamese hammered dulcimer', 'Recently imported into Vietnamese instruments, this thirty-six stringed dulcimer has many counterparts in various countries, such as santoor in India and cimbalon in Europe.'),
('501', 'aea9661c-cbda-4bf3-a61d-d78697472f29', 'rudra veena', '2', '0', '2019-01-08 23:11:21.58753+00', 'Ancient large North Indian tube zither', 'Considered the originator of all Indian strings (veena) it was used for ritual and meditation, North Indian raga and Dhrupad music. It has two dried gourd resonators and a body of bamboo with 24 wooden frets and 4 main, 2-3 secondary and one drone string.'),
('630', 'f1299271-c5d7-4f7c-8b72-d64aa152c3bb', 'setar', '2', '0', '2019-01-16 00:03:38.332157+00', 'Persian three-stringed long-necked lute', 'Derived from the Indian tritantri veena by the Persian poet Amir Khusro sometime in 13th century, it had 3 (now 4) strings and a long neck. It later gave name to the Indian sitar.'),
('548', '15cd573d-15a8-4f9f-a48f-f73218d85e14', 'suona', '1', '0', '2020-10-20 14:20:49.218757+00', 'Chinese double reed', 'Important to the folk music in northern China, it has a conical wooden body and seven finger holes.'),
('948', '404b8ce3-27c1-45b4-a5cf-86756b044b1d', 'boomwhacker', '3', '0', '2019-01-29 12:04:57.635695+00', 'Tuned hollow plastic tubes', 'Often used in group musical education and by street musicians, it consists of individual colourful hollow plastic tubes of various widths that are struck on various surfaces to produce sound, tubes can also be arranged and hit by mallets.'),
('128', '0d14d4e0-9ac9-4a96-a595-4145d7794082', 'carillon', '3', '0', '2019-08-13 07:35:31.072753+00', 'belfry tower bell set', 'Set of many bronze bells, often mechanized and operated by keyboard, they are set in the bell tower (belfry) of important buildings. <br /> For the steel bar metallophone used from toy to orchestra, see <a href=/instrument/340b8043-e3c4-443e-afb8-7fce24fe0ce4>glockenspiel</a>. <br /> For the crank operated, revolving cylinder/disc plucked idiophone see <a href=/instrument/2f5f6a67-2b2b-4857-92b0-5b25d485f632>music box</a>.'),
('917', '08450be5-f6d2-46d6-8be0-67087c02162c', 'baroque guitar', '2', '0', '2020-03-18 23:39:28.749892+00', 'Baroque gut string guitar', 'Predecessor of the modern classical guitar, it had gut strings and even gut frets. First described in 1555, it surpassed the Renaissance lutes popularity.'),
('955', '5e2209c2-4d1c-4eb3-9cbb-29fe7d6a2681', 'clapstick', '3', '0', '2019-02-04 22:16:49.32414+00', 'Ancient Aboriginal rhythm stick', 'Used by Australian Aboriginals to maintain rhythm in chants and traditionally to accompany didgeridoo. There are also Boomerang clapsticks.'),
('274', '3d7aca42-f7a7-46d8-9531-d39841a8aa6d', 'whistle', '1', '0', '2022-03-21 11:02:42.936574+00', 'Small simple single-toned flute', 'Simple, single-toned and round-bodied whistle often used for regulation and signalling (sport, traffic, ...).'),
('957', 'c641bccc-2060-4871-9c12-e2df2523e53c', 'paiban', '3', '0', '2019-02-05 21:33:43.274181+00', 'Ancient Chinese clapper', 'Made of sandalwood or bamboo, 2 blocks are tied together with a string, a third with a ribbon. Part of the drum and clapper ensemble guban, but confusingly, the clapper alone can also be called guban.'),
('915', '6efec29d-013a-4687-b710-fe25800eb358', 'string trio', '6', '0', '2023-12-13 20:28:53.563824+00', 'ensemble of violin, viola and cello', 'Chamber ensemble of three players (one violin, one viola, one cello).'),
('958', 'bf6af06a-5033-4af5-a6b8-7f235b0cff51', 'concussion idiophone', '3', '0', '2019-02-05 23:50:53.67477+00', '', 'Generally consists of two completely equal or somewhat unsymmetrical sticks, plates, shells or similar hit together.'),
('93', 'be34e4e5-6e77-46f5-ab56-c9641d3da213', 'viola da gamba', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:37:40.578765+00', 'generic member of the viol family, use for viol credits', 'The generic member of the viol family, use it for Viol credits, most viola da gamba credits are however the <a href=https://beta.musicbrainz.org/instrument/7cbd040f-6217-48d0-ac43-3e8ecb4b4b0b/>bass viol</a>.'),
('911', '2cb56c59-0eee-40ad-80b5-42594f49e760', 'piano trio', '6', '0', '2023-12-13 20:29:05.20739+00', 'ensemble of violin, cello and piano', 'Chamber ensemble of three players (one piano, one violin, one cello).'),
('966', 'ffafb925-3f23-4b29-a8f2-6bfa311ddd79', 'saluang', '1', '0', '2019-06-17 18:24:57.302443+00', 'West Sumatran end-blown flute.', 'Used traditionally by the Minang people of West Sumatra for love songs, in shamanic rites and for capturing tigers, this open end-blown bamboo flute can be decorated to resemble tiger-stripes. Played with a circular breathing technique, it is 75 cm long with 3 to 6 holes depending on subtype. <br /> <ul> <li>saluang darek inland 4 holes</li> <li>saluang pauh/padang 6 holes</li> <li>saluang sungai pagu 3 holes</li> </ul>'),
('1204', '2306cbdc-35b0-4ac0-8a86-cde04abb9b85', 'dūdmaišis', '1', '0', '2024-03-22 14:23:44.145534+00', 'Lithuanian bagpipe', 'It has a single chanter and drone with a bag made of a variety of animals, it has fur out and an ornamental goats head. Traditionally played at spring festivities, recently it has had a resurgence.'),
('989', '9b3d2812-e676-40de-902c-73c7769fb4f2', 'kendang', '3', '0', '2019-10-22 09:13:34.76019+00', 'Family of two sided laced drums used in various gamelan', 'Used in many Southeast Asian countries, the body is made of woods like jackfruit or coconut, the heads of buffalo- and goat-hide.<br /> There are 2 main groups:<br /> <ul> <li>The Java/Sunda set of 3 to 4 curve sided drums with heads of different sizes.</li> <li>The Bali set of two pairs of straight sided drums, both heads same size. </li> </ul>'),
('956', 'a30e17d9-505d-48df-ae38-16c47879bc2b', 'guban', '6', '0', '2019-05-13 09:55:47.291509+00', 'Traditional chinese drum and clapper.', 'Important in Yue, Kunkqu and Peking opera, it consists of the drum <a href=/instrument/42349583-c10d-4c6e-b553-28d916113856>bangu</a> and the clapper <a href=/instrument/c641bccc-2060-4871-9c12-e2df2523e53c>paiban</a>. Drum is played by one hand and clapper with the other.'),
('203', '29b024c3-f6cd-4415-83ec-2b6765856881', 'cornett', '1', '0', '2023-06-06 07:10:49.495437+00', 'Wooden medieval wind instrument', 'Popular from 1500 to 1650, also known as zink, it was octagonal with seven holes like flute but mouthpiece like trumpet.<br /> For the modern brass instrument, see <a href=/instrument/257dad59-02e6-47d9-958a-659843737827>cornet</a>.'),
('1001', '33e7df58-014a-4af6-95cd-62fda521c688', 'kacapi indung', '2', '0', '2019-11-06 21:57:54.948256+00', 'Boat shaped zither used in Sundanese gamelan', 'Known as indung mother or parahu boat, it has 18 brass strings each with its own pyramid shaped bridge. Shaped like a boat, its sound hole is at the bottom.'),
('497', '43c68c41-8b93-4330-b1af-524705ec289e', 'wind chime', '3', '0', '2019-08-18 12:12:34.723064+00', 'Wind played chimes', 'It differs from other chimes by addition of pendulum(s), such to be worked by wind, the sonorous parts can be rods, bells or other shapes of metal, wood, glass or ceramic.<br /> Often decorated, it is seen as a good luck charm.'),
('1011', '3dbbb5ff-103b-4260-8cf6-679a73a7c552', 'Indonesian rebab', '2', '0', '2020-02-03 09:53:35.570629+00', 'Indonesian spike-fiddle used in gamelan', 'Introduced to Indonesia in the 15th century, this variant of the spike-fiddle rebab has two bowed metal strings with characteristically long tuning pegs and is made of hide-covered wood or coconut shell. It is the melody leader in gamelan and is also used in healing rituals.'),
('338', '3b8cd68b-aadc-4e43-a13f-e575202d67ea', 'chimes', '3', '0', '2019-08-18 15:49:08.580028+00', 'Arrangement of hanging struck tuned metal rods.', 'Bar or pole shaped chimes, usually arranged in a line or circle, hanging free or struck with mallets. <br /> For the instrument often used in bell towers, see <a href=/instrument/0d14d4e0-9ac9-4a96-a595-4145d7794082>carillon</a>.<br /> For the instrument used in orchestra, see <a href=/instrument/7d6964ff-b1f5-472b-bdd7-b53de3739ad3>tubular bells</a>.'),
('597', '7f025c8a-cfe8-4ac7-844a-346877fb2607', 'saron family', '3', '0', '2019-11-22 04:43:12.046459+00', 'Family of Sundanese metallophones', 'Part of the Sundanese gamelan, these consist of a decorated wood resonator (rancak) upon which is resting six to nine thick, smooth, bronze or iron keys that are hit with mallets of hard wood or buffalo horn. <br /><br /> The saron family consists of the smallest member; saron panerus, the middle pitch member; saron barung and the largest member; sarong demung. Additionally, the largely obsolete slentho (which has been subsumed by the slenthem) is even deeper than the demung and the saron peking, which is a special slendro variant is even higher than the panerus, of which it shares an overlapping range. Finally the saron wayang is used in wayang performances.'),
('1009', 'b3fe02dc-f412-464e-b216-8c3fe45de456', 'saron peking', '3', '0', '2019-12-02 22:21:01.764447+00', 'Highest pitch saron-family member.', 'Similar to panerus with which it has a different but overlapping range, it has 6 bronze keys tuned for the slendro key.'),
('365', 'a26a663e-3add-42e1-ac07-ce289d5f330a', 'gamelan', '6', '0', '2019-11-22 04:41:38.39194+00', 'Indonesian traditional ensemble', 'Gamelan is basically split up in 3 traditions: the Balinese, the Sundanese and the Javanese, with each area having several different gamelan ensembles from large to small, each including a variety of instruments.<br /> Most if not all gamelan instruments come in two scales, Sléndro and Pélog, these are tuned differently and large gamelan orchestras always include at-least one of each scale and often several sets in each.<br /> Gamelan is an integrated part of Indonesian culture, is used in important traditions and throughout Indonesian life.'),
('1012', 'efa5b047-95e7-4ebb-9987-b07208a1ac27', 'bīn', '7', '0', '2020-02-26 23:05:05.171003+00', 'Family of ancient Indian stick zither chordophones', 'One of the two subfamilies of Indian chordophones, the North Indian stick zither used in classical Hindustani music has two (or more) large gourd sound resonators and a stick or tube body.<br /> Commonly called bin, been or bean, the representative is <a href=/instrument/aea9661c-cbda-4bf3-a61d-d78697472f29>rudra veena</a>, and credits to just bin are usually that.'),
('638', 'ddc0d7a5-cadb-4598-ac8d-83e17bde9816', 'chime bar', '3', '0', '2019-08-18 18:08:13.668698+00', 'Individual percussion plates.', 'Despite the name, it is not a chime but instead consists of tuned metal bars each on individual resonator boxes. <br /> It is similar to glockenspiel. <br /> For the instrument called <em>bar chimes</em>, see <a href=/instrument/3b8cd68b-aadc-4e43-a13f-e575202d67ea>chimes</a>.'),
('973', '12937176-5f04-4c8e-b75a-56f18754684e', 'reyong', '3', '0', '2019-08-21 23:13:08.175684+00', 'Gong-chime used in Balinese gamelan', 'Set of 4 to 12 small metal gongs suspended in a string carriage, played by two to four players.'),
('1027', 'e46bffd3-15a3-426a-923f-705839128609', 'viol consort', '6', '0', '2020-12-03 16:06:34.97969+00', 'ensemble of multiple viols', 'Ensemble of multiple instruments of the viol family, usually including at least treble, tenor and bass viols.'),
('770', 'bd57c6a6-616b-4c00-bcde-f0f34e8d6eb0', 'dulzaina', '1', '0', '2023-09-12 14:31:42.838224+00', 'Spanish traditional oboe', 'Not to be confused by the European renaissance bassoon <a href=/instrument/a0b1ba6b-6ea7-4489-a4af-c9e23d6e24da>dulcian</a>.<br /> Not to be confused with several Spanish bagpipes also called gaita.<br /> Widely used in Spanish communities it has many different names and a conical shape.'),
('1022', 'eafabec6-af67-4a49-be38-4401e7200494', 'melophone', '1', '0', '2023-12-13 19:18:51.600916+00', 'Bellowed free reed in a lute-like casing', 'Not to be confused with <a href=/instrument/6a539558-5585-4803-a705-a4520f23189d>mellophone</a>, a brass valved instrument.<br /> Wooden body shaped like a lute, it has a bellow operated by a handle at the bottom and buttons operating the reeds in the “neck”.'),
('1026', 'd43c2380-efe5-4488-b08f-777296d0c95c', 'pluriarc', '2', '0', '2020-12-03 13:09:17.629619+00', 'bow lute from West Africa', 'From West Africa, it has multiple curved necks each with one string, sometimes played a harp and sometimes with stops like a lute.'),
('340', '0d2ef84f-197b-405b-9a7c-293bbe331e30', 'shakers', '3', '0', '2019-02-27 15:29:47.971122+00', 'Latin-American tube rattle', 'Tube made of metal or bamboo, it is filled with seeds, pebbles or sand. Especially used in Latin American music, it is shaken rhythmically to produce sound.'),
('141', '0a06dd9a-92d6-4891-a699-2b116a3d3f37', 'other instruments', '5', '0', '2019-05-13 09:56:10.521853+00', '', 'Other instruments. If you cant find an instrument, please <a href=/doc/How_to_Add_Instruments>request it</a>.'),
('740', '6682190e-1ead-40cf-903f-76cbe351c019', 'çevgen', '3', '0', '2019-08-14 23:00:32.21248+00', 'Ceremonial Ottoman jangle-staff', 'Originating in Central Asia, it gained symbolic value to the Turks who used it in Ottoman marching-bands. It is 2-2,5 m long, has a bronze crescent shape with bells and jangles attached.'),
('747', '74dd2d22-adf6-4536-b290-8a20b51cf77f', 'akete', '3', '0', '2019-08-18 14:46:58.095979+00', 'set of Nyabinghi drums', 'Three-parts drumset (<a href=/instrument/ed1628bd-8541-4874-b8ca-2cec8b4c5140>baandu</a>, <a href=/instrument/81b68590-5c82-47a3-9790-1570ca60f711>funde</a> and <a href=/instrument/30aeef52-3ebf-405e-9baa-ef6c6f3ef6d5>kete</a>) commonly used in Burru and Nyabinghi musics.'),
('934', '06b3aae9-ad08-4607-9ea3-767b5dee897b', 'The Great Stalacpipe Organ', '3', '0', '2019-08-27 07:59:07.968179+00', 'electrically actuated lithophone', 'Located in the Luray Caverns of Virginia USA, it is made of an electric console wired to mallets striking thirty-seven stalactites producing tones. This is a singular specific instrument, not an instrument <em>type</em>.'),
('975', 'dededbf9-ee13-496a-9903-29d70d11452c', 'kantilan', '3', '0', '2019-09-02 16:56:36.732757+00', 'High pitch gangsa used in Balinese gamelan', 'Highest pitched gangsa, it has 10 brass or bronze keys suspended over short resonating bamboo pipes set in an heavily ornate case.'),
('967', 'dda8aef8-a19f-4026-bb0d-f4e617125e94', 'ugal', '3', '0', '2019-09-02 17:41:46.173493+00', 'Deep pitch gangsa used in Balinese gamelan', 'Even lower pitched than the pemade , it also has 10 bronze keys suspended over tuned bamboo resonators that the player hits with a small hammer, often in a theatrical manner. It is the leader of the pokok melody.'),
('977', '75bca310-73ac-484d-9f2b-5dcdf3915bab', 'gambang', '3', '0', '2019-09-03 14:48:22.143255+00', 'Indonesian wood box-resonated xylophone', 'Consists of up to 21 hardwood bars suspended by pins and rope over an oft ornate wooden trapeze shaped box, the two springy beaters are made of buffalo horn.'),
('978', '8c4382b9-33ee-48d2-b1ad-edb8ce0da05d', 'kecer', '3', '0', '2019-09-09 17:12:50.737739+00', 'Indonesian racked cymbals', 'Used in both gamelan and Wayang puppet theatre, it consists of two small cymbals sets; the bottom pair affixed in a highly decorated rancak rack, their lose counterparts attached together by string.'),
('756', '4af93445-7eea-4253-aa61-afade8fb43d7', 'garifuna drum', '3', '0', '2019-10-04 23:16:41.692005+00', '', 'Important to the Garifuna culture, it consists of two drums, the tenor, primero and the bass, segunda, each is made of hollowed out wood with membranes of pig, sheep or deer.'),
('1010', '3b7be43c-0b3b-42dd-8560-d61e41f6bd61', 'saron wayang', '3', '0', '2019-12-02 22:36:36.829616+00', 'Special saron used for Wayang puppetry', 'Used in the Javanese Wayang puppet theatre, it has nine large bronze keys set in a decorated frame.'),
('981', 'b3203b9f-327a-4d7e-97f7-5e783e5b99a1', 'gong-chime', '3', '0', '2019-09-20 19:00:21.632199+00', 'Arrangement of kettle shaped gongs', 'Chiefly used in Southeast Asian music, these consist of from only 1 to several dozens of metal (often bronze) kettles, set in a wide variety of different supports and played with mallets.'),
('984', 'e0350378-0d4b-49d5-ad81-8f74e1b54efc', 'kempul', '3', '0', '2019-10-07 13:22:00.582968+00', 'Javanese hanging gong-set', 'Set of 6 to 10 smaller hanging pitched bronze gongs with a protruding centre knob struck with tabuh beaters. Higher pitched than the gong ageng, it is often hung together with it.'),
('982', '2c235622-4671-4112-9c1d-0550125db907', 'kempli', '3', '0', '2019-10-01 21:43:53.607381+00', 'Singular metal timekeeping gong-chime used in Balinese gamelan', 'Singular bronze gong-chime kettle set on a decorated jackfruit-wood box stand. Used as time or tempo keeper, it is struck on the boss with panggul beater, which provides reference point in the pokok.'),
('716', '06aaeafb-8dce-468f-8b46-7607a30438cb', 'swarmandal', '2', '0', '2019-10-03 09:24:40.388599+00', 'North Indian trapezoid board zither', 'Used chiefly in classical Indian songstyles Khyal and Thumri, it has a trapezoid shape with up to 40 metal strings fastened at both sides by iron pegs with one side having tuning keys.'),
('1206', 'c1ab8f12-4168-47ce-821c-5002d7089565', 'neyanban', '1', '0', '2024-03-23 19:21:35.016614+00', 'Iranian single reed bagpipe', 'Often colourfully decorated, it is known since ancient times in southern Persia. It has a single reed with a double piped chanter with 6-7 holes.'),
('971', '7e024f24-f778-4942-8fba-6f33ebfb2ac6', 'bonang panerus', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:47:42.782201+00', 'Highest pitched gong-chime set in Javanese gamelan', 'Used to play fast melodies, it is the highest pitched member of the bonang family of gong-chimes.'),
('986', 'beb10494-f892-4865-b2aa-9f4c21824ee0', 'kethuk', '3', '0', '2019-10-14 09:08:49.573546+00', 'Small boxed gong-chime used in Javanese gamelan', 'Always used with kempyang, it consists of a single bronze kettle-gong, pitched deeper than kempyangs. Flat top bossed gong is sat in a highly decorated rancak frame, beaten with tabuh beaters by the same person.'),
('991', '176ce29f-bcf0-47f5-beda-c97ef6df6480', 'kendhang ketipung', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:56:11.458405+00', 'Smallest conical kendang used in both Javanese/Sundanese gamelan', 'Smallest of the kendang, it is has a special two-instrument use with the <a href=/instrument/14acd267-2e1b-459d-b41e-058d2c106345>gendhing</a>.<br /> In Sunda it is known as kendhang katipung.'),
('988', 'dd430e7f-36ba-49a5-825b-80a525e69190', 'kemanak', '3', '0', '2019-10-14 14:36:03.669053+00', 'Banana shaped bronze slit-drum used in javanese gamelan', 'Bent into a ladle or banana like shape, it is a pair of bronze slit-drums hit with tabuh beaters.'),
('559', '57be0c41-d871-424d-a4e0-db6d5cbb6aea', 'tap dance', '3', '0', '2019-10-20 15:00:33.74926+00', '', 'Tap dancing is a type of dance in which the dancer wears special shoes that make a clicking sound as the dancers feet strike the floor.'),
('985', '17ea56e2-44b2-4331-a368-54a5849074b0', 'kenong', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:55:48.864339+00', 'Large high-pitch gong-chime used in Indonesian Gamelan', 'Related to bonang, it consists of 3 decorated rancak frames that each hold 2 large arched (jaler) bronze gong-chimes hit by heavy tabuh beater(s).'),
('990', '14acd267-2e1b-459d-b41e-058d2c106345', 'kendhang gendhing', '3', '0', '2019-10-20 22:20:32.275419+00', 'Largest conical kendang used in both Javanese/Sundanese gamelan', 'Largest or ageng of the kendang, it is still smaller than the <a href=/instrument/9063d25e-87e4-4adc-81d4-8fdee23bd26f>bedug</a>.<br /> In Sunda it is known as kendhang gedé.'),
('996', 'c588cc24-e139-44a9-8a48-7963eb693dd1', 'kendhang indung', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:56:15.466733+00', 'King-Size truncated cone kendang used in Sundanese gamelan', 'Played in ensemble with kulanter, it is set at an angle and played with hands or sticks. It has the designation of mother.'),
('992', 'f6b76abc-fdef-444c-97b1-27b12e3e3c0b', 'kendhang batangan', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:56:18.972328+00', 'Middle conical kendang used in both Javanese/Sundanese gamelan', 'Middle sized kendang, it is used in lively and complex rhythms. <br /> In Sunda it is known as kendhang ciblon.'),
('979', '1c4ab081-1500-4372-9820-cbd1f93325c4', 'jegogan', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:57:01.87179+00', 'Deepest pitch gangsa used in Balinese gamelan', 'Largest and lowest pitched of the gangsa, it has 5 to 7 large metal bars suspended over long bamboo resonators.'),
('954', 'bd734382-68be-4b7b-adbd-cbdf35cdf740', 'shaken idiophone', '3', '0', '2019-03-06 16:00:36.776012+00', '', 'Shaken idiophone or rattle. Sound is produced by holding or containing usually small concussing parts.'),
('959', 'a2783aac-898d-48a3-a7fd-34457cccf10a', 'percussion idiophone', '3', '0', '2019-03-15 22:00:31.266939+00', '', 'Generally consists of one to very many plates, sticks, or other objects hit with (or against) various types of mallets.'),
('962', '73173277-b7ef-4d5e-83b2-205cd2f12488', 'slenthem', '3', '0', '2019-11-11 16:48:48.224209+00', 'Deepest pitch single octave metallophone used in Javanese gamelan', 'Used in Javanese gamelan, the 6(slendro)-7(pelog) bronze keys beat by a disk mallet(tabuh) are suspended above individual tube metal/bamboo resonators set in a 75 cm long wooden frame.'),
('943', 'a4711cb9-800f-4b6b-b7fc-23fd1d494d9b', 'veena', '7', '0', '2020-02-27 17:45:01.52399+00', 'Family of ancient Indian lute-like chordophones', 'One of the two subfamilies of Indian chordophones, the South Indian gourd lute used in classical Carnatic music has a single gourd music-box (sometimes a secondary small resonator gourd) with an often hollow neck.<br /> Commonly called just veena or vina, the representative is <a href=/instrument/41761936-5dbc-433f-b558-a7ef14fe9b08>Saraswati veena</a>, and credits to just veena are usually that.'),
('899', '8f15287f-48c1-4a7c-a7f7-30653c490279', 'viol family', '7', '0', '2019-05-13 09:56:50.21801+00', 'Viola de gamba family', 'Please use <a href=/instrument/be34e4e5-6e77-46f5-ab56-c9641d3da213>Viola da Gamba</a> with credit viol for generic / unspecified viol credits, and not this one. Developed in the 15th century from vihuelists starting to play with bows, viols have frets, flat backs, sloped shoulders, c-holes and are tuned in fourths.'),
('961', '580a5cdd-920a-43f9-bb0a-981cf357d96c', 'gendèr', '7', '0', '2019-11-11 17:16:50.944342+00', 'Family of Indonesian metallophones', 'Uses in Javanese gamelan and Balinese wayang, these range from 12 to 14 tuned bronze keys, all suspended over metal or bamboo resonators.'),
('880', 'ed1628bd-8541-4874-b8ca-2cec8b4c5140', 'baandu', '3', '0', '2019-08-18 14:47:59.483833+00', 'Nyabinghi bass drum', 'Larger bass drum also known as thunder or pope smasher, it has a double goat skin membrane and is hit with a padded mallet. Important in the Jamaican Burru music and Rastafari movement, it is part of the Nyabinghi/Akete drums.'),
('947', '6ceaa056-1bfd-470e-ae4a-320e1428648a', 'kachva sitar', '2', '0', '2020-03-04 21:42:47.182988+00', 'Flat-cut gourd sitar', 'Flat-cut gourd sitar with 16 frets, 2 steel & 3 brass strings. In the 1820s it was used by Ghulam Mohammed to develop the surbahar.<br /><br /> Mistakenly re-named Kachapi vina in the 19th century by Tagore, that instrument was actually an ancient unrelated short-necked pear-shaped lute.'),
('976', '8dd31b5e-a96e-4bf8-8f55-59930bb89dc9', 'pemade', '3', '0', '2019-09-02 22:31:51.762259+00', 'Lower pitch gangsa used in Balinese gamelan', 'Second highest pitched gangsa, it is deeper than the kantil but also has 10 brass or bronze keys suspended over short resonating pipes set in an heavily ornate case.'),
('970', '93ccd14f-9629-403f-8e5c-993621a7c290', 'bonang barung', '3', '0', '2019-09-20 04:09:36.126339+00', 'Medium pitched gong-chime set in Javanese gamelan', 'One to two octaves below <a href=/instrument/7e024f24-f778-4942-8fba-6f33ebfb2ac6>panerus</a>, it plays elaborate melodies and is one of the most important instruments in the ensemble.'),
('349', '906e1945-bfcb-4952-bba5-f43296d7aff6', 'metallophone', '7', '0', '2019-09-20 18:59:39.455102+00', 'Arrangement of struck tuned metal bars.', 'Consisting of tuned metal bars, slates or keys struck with mallets and arranged (often on resonators of sonorous material) in various scales. Compare <a href=/instrument/db95a035-6a3d-44b4-8694-74ff71b61768>xylophone</a> for the wooden bar equivalent.'),
('987', 'e42151f8-efb2-41e1-9aad-fb8fa115c233', 'kempyang', '3', '0', '2019-10-14 09:09:20.005883+00', 'Small boxed double gong-chime used in Javanese gamelan', 'Always used with ketuk, it consists of two bronze kettle-gongs, pitched a note apart. Ached top bossed gongs are sat in the highly decorated rancak frame, beaten with tabuh beaters by the same person.'),
('993', '4ac4b541-116d-40c1-93c7-160153ca53ac', 'kendhang wayangan', '3', '0', '2019-10-21 17:04:30.61837+00', 'Middle conical kendang used in javanese gamelan', 'Middle sized kendang, it was traditionally used for the wayang dance.'),
('997', '292a95fd-9bc7-4052-aa6e-844c8f4f4905', 'kendhang kulanter', '3', '0', '2019-10-22 10:57:58.842214+00', 'Paired truncated cone kendang used in Sundanese gamelan', 'Always used together with the <a href=/instrument/c588cc24-e139-44a9-8a48-7963eb693dd1>indung</a>, dual child drums are divided into the katipung (besar or larger) and the kutiplak (kecil or smaller).'),
('998', 'd5daaae4-fc89-41ac-a0b5-44b336bfa513', 'kepyak', '3', '0', '2019-11-04 15:25:08.177275+00', 'Metal plate percussion used in Javanese gamelan', 'Used in wayang puppetry, it is made of 1 to 4 iron (sometimes bronze) plates hung by strings, The puppeteer uses a small mallet set in the foot to hit the plate(s).'),
('1002', '896bc919-e1db-4939-9555-857f5727faa8', 'kacapi rincik', '2', '0', '2019-11-06 22:01:31.266571+00', 'Small boat shaped zither used in Sundanese gamelan', 'Known as rincik child it has 15 steel strings, it has individual bridges and a sound-hole in the bottom.'),
('964', '30d1a6e4-84e7-4e59-94d2-bcf148cadb32', 'slentho', '3', '0', '2019-12-02 21:35:10.402794+00', 'Obsolete deepest saron-family member used in Sundanese gamelan.', 'Unlike the other saron, its six-seven keys are not smooth, but bevelled or bossed, like the gendèr and the <a href=/instrument/73173277-b7ef-4d5e-83b2-205cd2f12488>slenthem</a>, which has largely replaced it in the modernised gamelan.'),
('1205', '63a3e51d-a27a-4304-8dd0-67f954004824', 'hümmelchen', '1', '0', '2024-03-27 20:04:53.085751+00', 'Small German Renaissance bagpipe', 'Having a small bag, it has a soft sound. Its chanter and two drones of differing length are made of fruitwood. It historically had single reeds, modern creations are more complex and double-reeded.'),
('592', '9478e40f-bab3-4fcb-a52a-f3df65770bfa', 'żummara', '5', '0', '2021-02-08 22:11:46.057634+00', 'Maltese mirliton', 'Made of bamboo with one end covered with grease-paper, it is a side-blown mirliton.<br /> Not to be confused with the Egyptian/Iraqi zummara which is an instrument similar to a chalumeau.'),
('1028', '3cfca17d-eb2c-4b40-9a9a-ca3111a55b54', 'keyed box zither', '2', '0', '2023-12-13 19:31:26.013622+00', 'Composite chordophone', 'Composite chordophone, box zither where some or all strings are operated by typewriter-keys or buttons (keyboard).'),
('980', '395bab77-bb77-4696-96d6-dfcade201c6d', 'jublag', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:56:57.199878+00', 'Second deepest pitch gangsa used in Balinese gamelan', 'Second lowest pitched of the gangsa, it has 4 to 7 bronze keys suspended over long bamboo resonators.<br /> For the Sundanese bamboo xylophone also used in gamelan, see <a href=/instrument/6e180df5-6df9-46bb-8ebf-c576a010fb5a>calung</a>.'),
('1031', 'ebf1c87b-b936-47e1-9a67-bd28c2bbdca6', 'stick zither', '2', '0', '2021-02-08 16:16:13.369983+00', '', 'Class of instruments where the body is a simple stick with one to many strings attached, may also have up to several usually gourd or wood resonators.'),
('370', '760558ba-a02a-4692-9046-b819cf75836f', 'sistrum', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 20:02:36.018483+00', 'Ancient Egyptian rattle', 'Used in sacred rituals, it is made of metal or clay rattle with metal discs which jangle when shook. <br/> Not to be confused with the West African calabash sistrum or disc rattle (ngoso mbara).'),
('817', '68a64027-1bc3-4057-bd51-165697322aca', 'kamale ngɔni', '2', '0', '2021-02-08 22:14:34.85344+00', 'Modern ngoni made of calabash with more strings', 'Modern derivative of the donso ngɔni, it comes with more strings and is made of calabash. It became an important instrument in the rise of the Wassoulou music in the 80s and 90s.'),
('408', 'b4f112c3-d666-47f2-bb85-bae28572ca13', 'shawm', '1', '0', '2024-01-25 20:53:33.159598+00', '12th century to present double reed woodwind', 'Not to be confused with zummara or other double clarinets with similar names.<br /> For the multiple bore free reed created in 1880, see Martinshorn.<br /> For the similarly named single-reed woodwind, see <a href=/instrument/e3511ed1-3d73-4340-880f-c8ccc8eda11c>chalumeau</a>.<br /> For the Japanese descendant named from Portuguese, see <a href=/instrument/07b91470-b63e-41e4-88e6-11c4acac064f>charumera</a>.<br /> For the Catalan shawm, see <a href=/instrument/dffe56f5-cd75-4392-ad31-1c3abf2b8e37> tible</a>.<br /> For the Italian ciaramella, see <a href=/instrument/814816db-3368-4889-a8cd-aa34bd1043f0>piffero</a>.<br /> For the bagpipe, see <a href=/instrument/21d5d4ec-f8ef-44dc-b02f-e564de057dcc> xeremies</a>.<br /><br /> European medieval and Renaissance conical bore double-reed woodwind, two types evolved; one from Middle-Eastern instruments and one from bagpipe chanters. A combination of both were used to develop the modern oboe.'),
('267', '22fc02a8-0f6e-4b69-895b-b4db47cc8eac', 'wooden fish', '3', '0', '2021-01-23 13:05:53.3787+00', 'wooden bell used in temples', 'Highly stylised wooden block-bell, it is used in religious ritual. Its prototype, fish board (gyoban) is more obviously shaped like a fish.'),
('1030', '9a808a67-a3ca-4690-9b55-05f10d237ba5', 'hummel', '2', '0', '2021-01-25 16:56:14.853763+00', 'Medieval pear-shaped drone zither', 'Whole or half-pear shaped wooden body, it is partly fretted and has two string-courses; melody and drone. The name comes from Germanic words meaning bumblebee or buzzing.'),
('366', '1a03e9a1-f81f-40ce-9d57-65d6c1b9dcb3', 'slit drum', '3', '0', '2021-01-26 13:27:44.435222+00', 'Hollow wooden idiophone', 'Made of hollowed out wood or bamboo, it has incisions or slits as soundholes. Slit drums are among the most ancient and earliest instruments.'),
('755', 'c3ff2412-ea4e-4299-b93e-ca011c647dde', 'quijada', '3', '0', '2023-12-13 19:53:43.271297+00', 'Jawbone rattle', 'Made of an equine jawbone, it is used in traditional Latin American music as a rattle.'),
('555', '1975ee04-30de-4835-9656-102ccd49c0c7', 'taishogoto', '2', '0', '2021-01-28 17:19:13.178466+00', 'Japanese keyed box zither', 'Developed in the early Taisho period to modernise the ningenkin, it has metal strings and typewriter like keys with a wooden lid over the frets.'),
('108', '33b6ba89-8265-4d8f-bbdc-ecff41e29e8c', 'cabasa', '3', '0', '2021-02-02 17:04:45.180106+00', 'Modern wood and metal-bead shaker', 'Developed from the African agbe, a small shaker not unlike shekere, it is made of wood and metal, with metal beads.'),
('710', '041e4a26-8ddb-45dc-961a-23bcf6e0615b', 'mukkuri', '3', '0', '2023-03-31 11:39:20.636589+00', 'Ainu mouth harp', 'Ingenious to the Ainu, it is made of bamboo with a string that vibrated creates sound.'),
('612', 'b4d38ac1-7f12-437c-a61a-be2796ffc559', 'vichitra veena', '2', '0', '2021-02-08 17:04:12.282473+00', 'Large North Indian fretless sliding tube zither', 'Played like a slide guitar, it has two large gourd resonators with a teak body that often ends in carved peacock heads. Fretless, it has 4 main, 5 chikari and 13 resonance strings, slide is a glass orb named batta.'),
('1207', '5f948a81-90ce-4d4a-b1d8-863ff1052c88', 'parkapzuk', '1', '0', '2024-04-09 18:38:14.528466+00', 'Armenian double chanter bagpipe', 'Has a bag made of goat, veal or sheepskin, and a double piped chanter collected in a single horn. Both wooden chanters have holes; one for melody, the other for drone.'),
('251', '75ef0f2e-0ca2-48ef-9a1c-56f23a900652', 'đàn bầu', '2', '0', '2021-02-08 22:15:09.358409+00', 'One-string Vietnamese tube zither', 'Possibly ancient Vietnamese tube zither. It was originally made of bamboo with one silken string, today it is usually wooden with a metal string. Fastened in one end to a movable device and resonator, the melody comes from changing the strings tension.'),
('175', '563a9f16-e84b-409a-bda5-2e4ce09d5573', 'clavinet', '2', '0', '2021-04-14 19:59:17.015295+00', 'Electro-mechanical amplified clavichord', 'Originally produced by Hohner from 1964 to 1982, it had keys with rubber-clad metal tines that tapped metal strings and two electric pickups. Its sound has been recreated in many modern synths.'),
('528', '0ddf2bbb-18bb-41da-b369-f145fc17fa50', 'bulbul tarang', '2', '0', '2021-02-09 15:36:33.894525+00', 'Indian keyed box zither', 'Developed from the Japanese <a href=/instrument/1975ee04-30de-4835-9656-102ccd49c0c7>taishogoto</a>, it is made of wood, often an integral case. It has two courses of strings; drone and melody strings operated by buttons or keys.'),
('1208', 'e1a801ee-da51-469f-94c0-8522aaffb631', 'mashak', '1', '0', '2024-04-24 15:49:56.381948+00', 'Northern Indian bagpipe', 'Used in rural weddings, it has twin single reed pipes, one melody, one drone. It is becoming increasingly rare due to being displaced by Scottish Highland pipes.'),
('1032', 'b52a98c1-150f-4bde-9ac4-f44c528fc514', 'jantar', '2', '0', '2021-02-11 09:55:10.317648+00', 'Rajasthani stick zither', 'Stick zither from Rajasthan. It is made of wood with at least two large gourd resonators, the strings rest on very high frets. <br /><br /> Not to be confused with the 13th century tritantri-vina which evolved into the bin via a five-string stick-zither also known as jantar.'),
('744', '5ecc4a53-28eb-415e-81b0-79d5ab5b310c', 'chitra veena', '2', '0', '2021-02-12 19:12:35.202512+00', 'Large South Indian fretless Carnatic slide lute', '13th century or earlier South Indian fretless slide lute used in Carnatic music. Hollow body made of jack-fruit with a secondary resonator of hollowed out gourd, it has 6 main, 3 drone and 11-12 sympathetic strings with a sliding block of hardwood to vary pitch. Much like the North Indian <a href=/instrument/b4d38ac1-7f12-437c-a61a-be2796ffc559>vichitra veena</a> is to the <a href=/instrument/aea9661c-cbda-4bf3-a61d-d78697472f29>rudra veena</a>, chitra veena is to the <a href=/instrument/41761936-5dbc-433f-b558-a7ef14fe9b08>Saraswati veena</a>.'),
('368', 'c6842ddb-3226-49c0-b7af-37ebc607dc85', 'frottoir', '3', '0', '2023-04-19 08:38:25.077173+00', 'Zydeco vest scraper', 'Dispenses with the frame altogether, and is worn as a vest, it is played with spoons or bottle openers.'),
('523', '3933adfe-f55b-47fd-b085-c9983d15cc9d', 'five-string banjo', '2', '0', '2021-11-04 06:01:15.565992+00', '', 'The most common and based on the original design, its fifth string is shorter than the others, creating an uneven pitch progression.'),
('78', '13300a83-2776-481a-80fb-cd68f7be4051', 'hardingfele', '2', '0', '2021-11-09 20:16:21.721899+00', '', 'Folk-fiddle from Hardanger, Norway. It has 4 melody- and 4-5 drone-strings, it is richly decorated and used in the traditional halling folk music and dance.'),
('62', '089f123c-0f7d-4105-a64e-49de81ca8fa4', 'violin', '2', '0', '2021-11-04 15:33:33.580302+00', 'Soprano of modern violin family', 'The most famous member of the violin family, it is actually the small viol. Its register is soprano and its a principal member of the symphony orchestra.'),
('96', 'b8471d2e-9b9d-4f52-822e-b19a37cd30ac', 'washtub bass', '2', '0', '2023-04-25 18:33:53.484101+00', 'Improvised monochord', 'Consisting of a stick, a string and an resonator of various materials, it is used in many countries low-cost and DIY cultures. Its technically a variable tension chordophone.'),
('60', '0db03a60-1142-4b25-ab1b-72027d0dc357', 'cello', '2', '0', '2021-11-09 20:15:32.555845+00', 'Small bass of modern violin family', 'Also know as violoncello (the small large viol), it is the medium bass member of the modern violin family and a principal member of the symphony orchestra.'),
('451', '984e4a24-7d34-4661-a6e4-0a28374ff89f', 'Stroh violin', '2', '0', '2021-11-09 20:16:53.644572+00', 'Horn-amplified violin', 'Instead of a wooden body, it is amplified by a metal horn resonator; its louder and more directional sound made it useful in loud areas.'),
('63', '377e007a-33fe-4825-9bef-136cf5cf581a', 'viola', '2', '0', '2021-11-09 20:17:45.937947+00', 'Alto of modern violin family', 'It is known by many names, based on the full alto de viola da braccio: alto, bratsch (braccio), viola, etc. <br /> It is the alto member of the modern violin family and a principal member of the symphony orchestra.'),
('1034', '54fc9c17-b16f-4d10-a372-c3f1bb6da70f', 'string synthesizer', '4', '0', '2021-11-22 18:59:45.596042+00', '60-80s electronic string-ensemble emulator', 'Developed from the 1960s and used mainly in the 70-80s, it was a cheaper and more portable simplification of the mellotron, emulating string ensembles. Its later hybrid development with the electronic organ created polyphonic ensemble synthesizers.'),
('1071', '091ecfa0-a0b7-405c-b14c-82806cccc465', 'bombo legüero', '3', '0', '2022-08-09 16:29:06.798189+00', 'Andean bass-drum', 'Used in folklore music of Andes, it is a descendant of European bass drum. It has a shoulder strap and two soft headed mallets used to strike the goat or llama pelt membrane.'),
('469', '0d6efd24-2fe8-4a46-b34d-46633e30f642', 'soprano recorder', '1', '0', '2022-03-03 17:18:52.532739+00', 'Middle member of the end-blown fipple flute recorder family', 'Also known as the descant, it is the third smallest and most common member of the modern recorder family. <br /> Traditionally made of various woods, it is today often made of plastic and used to teach children music. <br /> Not to be confused with the side-blown (concerto) <a href=/instrument/b524b7a7-2d87-43a7-9977-8a9081ff6e0f/>soprano flute</a>.'),
('569', '448eeddf-37a3-49f3-9e46-d46ccd821aaf', 'siku', '1', '0', '2024-01-22 17:24:19.554048+00', 'Andean double row panpipe', 'For the Italian bagpipe, see <a href=/instrument/7186ac40-8154-49d0-8d24-33efd8c2a41e>zampogna</a>.<br /> Also known as zampona, traditional Andean panpipe has two rows of pipes tied together with colourful bands.'),
('18', '3cf4c0c9-160a-4d73-9243-7d0e0df17050', 'recorder', '1', '0', '2022-03-08 19:52:10.909424+00', 'Family of end-blown fipple flutes', 'Family of end-blown woodwind flutes with a thumb-hole and seven finger-holes, it is the most common flute in Western classical tradition. <br /> The family consists of a wide assortment of sizes:<br /> <ul> <li>garklein recorder</li> <li>sopranino recorder</li> <li>soprano recorder (descant)</li> <li>alto recorder (treble)</li> <li>tenor recorder</li> <li>bass recorder</li> <li>great bass recorder (c-bass)</li> <li>contrabass recorder</li> <li>subcontrabass recorder</li> </ul> <br /> Not to be confused with the transverse (side-blown) Western concert flute.'),
('711', '73bf4431-d576-46d1-a1c3-158b4de0764d', 'wot', '1', '0', '2022-08-30 15:48:20.846463+00', 'Round Southeast Asian traditional pan-flute', 'Used in Laos and Isan traditional music, it is made of bamboo or ku wood, the individual stopped pipes are arranged around a central core using beeswax.'),
('298', 'ca17a349-e0e3-4b9b-b74d-898a2b54b43e', 'syrinx', '1', '0', '2022-08-30 15:49:10.729466+00', 'Ancient Greek pan flute', 'Named after the myth of the nymph Syrinx, this reed pan flute was used in ancient Greece.'),
('16', '6b5b72d8-6e9c-4e31-bd21-062d10bcf661', 'pan flute', '1', '0', '2022-08-30 15:49:40.864874+00', 'Collection of end-blown pipes', 'Named after the Greek god Pan, they are a selection of end-blown pipes made of reeds, bamboo, wood or similar. Many different variations exists around the world, especially in South America.'),
('54', '43f378cf-b099-46da-8ec3-a39b6f5e5258', 'classical guitar', '2', '0', '2022-09-01 11:00:34.586119+00', 'Modern acoustic gut/nylon string guitar', 'Also known as Spanish guitar, it is used in classical, folk and other styles, the strings are nylon or gut.'),
('1072', 'd6ac9f9f-2352-4aea-9a1a-dd8c8443c5e9', 'bell plate', '3', '0', '2022-09-22 09:24:01.576414+00', 'Set of tuned metal plates used in western orchestra', 'Used occasionally in the western classical orchestra and theatre, it consists of several tuned aluminium, steel or bronze plates, struck to imitate the sound of bells.'),
('361', '842d3d24-f638-47e6-a239-8578723db09c', 'diatonic button accordion', '1', '0', '2022-09-26 12:47:50.501404+00', 'Accordion with buttons arranged diatonically', 'For the organ also known as Melodeon, see <a href=/instrument/20443ce3-cde1-4968-b7cc-65e45bb9714f>reed organ</a>.<br /> For the mouth blown keyed MELODION, see <a href=/instrument/8ab40df2-106b-4b9b-a50c-0798ee95da8f>melodica</a>.<br /> Also known as Melodeon, it has 1 to 2 rows of buttons that each produce two tones (bisonoric).'),
('41', 'bdf08ac2-b9c2-4391-85e5-9a7716bdd690', 'accordion', '1', '0', '2022-09-29 16:35:51.676137+00', 'Commonly used bellowed free reed with keys/buttons', 'Invented and developed by several people in the early 1800s, it has an arm operated bellows with keys or buttons at one end and bass buttons at the other.'),
('1076', '025d1189-c74b-4f04-8ea0-c00c483b8296', 'pedal accordion', '1', '0', '2022-10-18 17:49:37.789742+00', 'Polish foot-pedal accordion', 'Developed in Warszaw, Poland, it is used in folk music. It has two foot-operated bellows attached via metal/brass pipe; its body-bellows are only used for accents.'),
('204', '20443ce3-cde1-4968-b7cc-65e45bb9714f', 'reed organ', '1', '0', '2022-10-11 19:07:19.328369+00', 'Organ with free reeds', 'For the accordion also known as Melodeon, see <a href=/instrument/842d3d24-f638-47e6-a239-8578723db09c>diatonic button accordion</a>.<br /> For the mouth blown keyed MELODION, see <a href=/instrument/8ab40df2-106b-4b9b-a50c-0798ee95da8f>melodica</a>.<br /> For the portable reed organ used in India see <a href=/instrument/c43c7647-077d-4d60-a01b-769de71b82f2>harmonium</a>.<br /> Also known as pump organ, it is large, looks like an upright piano and has pedals attached to bellows with reeds. Sound is produced by playing the keyboard.'),
('1074', '648deac1-43a7-4ea0-8ef4-b77d88eba354', 'flutina', '1', '0', '2022-10-18 17:50:27.106424+00', '', 'Early predecessor to the <a href=/instrument/842d3d24-f638-47e6-a239-8578723db09c>diatonic accordion</a>, it was similar to the German concertina and had 4 fold bellows and brass reeds.'),
('135', 'c43c7647-077d-4d60-a01b-769de71b82f2', 'harmonium', '1', '0', '2022-10-18 17:53:49.370295+00', 'Portable Indian reed organ', 'Not to be confused with European upright <a href=/instrument/20443ce3-cde1-4968-b7cc-65e45bb9714f>reed organ</a> also commonly known as Harmonium. <br /> Also known as the samvadini, it was developed in India from imported reed organs. Consists of a wooden box-shape with a keyboard and a bellows in the back; both are operated by the same player, often a singer. While upright versions exist, they are rare.'),
('1075', '3ec414ba-6b15-4a78-8ac0-d399eff41b3c', 'garmon', '1', '0', '2022-10-18 17:54:27.828713+00', 'Russian diatonic folk accordion', 'Used in Russian, Mari and Caucasus folk music, it has two rows of buttons in a diatonic scale, as well as additional bass buttons.');
